VALUES
(2278, 'en_US', 'Brotzeit German Bier Restaurant and Bar', 'Enjoy the Victoria Harbour view with authentic German cuisines and beers!', 'Emperor\'s Cake, Achyranthes, German Susage, Baked Pork Knuckle', '', 'Originated in Singapore since 2006, Brotzeit® is the world\'s only German franchise concept introducing a unique New German dining experience – premium German beers and authentic Bavarian cuisine in a chic and contemporary setting.
Located at Tsim Sha Tsui Centre on Mody Road in Tsim Sha Tsui East, the first outlet in Hong Kong is definitely one of the city\'s most exciting new dining destinations.', '10-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit P1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2290, 'en_US', 'Yakiniku Masamichi', 'Japanese BBQ in Causeway Bay, enjoy the melty Kagoshima A4 black cattle in Yakiniku Masamichi!', 'Kagoshima A4 Black Cattle, South African Abalone, Hokkaido Scallop.King Prawn, Alaska King Crab Legs, Sanuki Udon, Masamichi Sashimi Platter, Crab Roe Salad', '', 'Yakiniku Masamichi located in the heart of Causeway Bay. Restaurant offers different kinds of ingredient e.g wagyu, seafood and chicken etc. for you to enjoy the Japanese BBQ with competitive price and comfortable environment. Yakiniku Masamichi imports A4 Kagoshima Wagyu directly from Japan! Come and enjoy the tender and melty Wagyu here!
How to enjoy birthday promo at this restaurant
1. Book a table on your birthday (min. 2 people), and choose birthday as dining purpose.
2. Show up at the restaurant on the day of dining and show your ID to restaurant staff for verification.
3. Enjoy your birthday meal and don\'t forget to pay with EZTABLE!
4. You will receive your birthday gift in form of coupon code, two days after your dining! 
5. The amount of coupon is equal to your total dining amount divided by total diners, with maximum of HKD 500. 
6. Coupon code will be valid for your next dining at any restaurants with Checkout service and is valid for 30 days.', '4-min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit C', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2302, 'en_US', 'Chef Studio by Eddy', 'Chef Eddy serves best seasonal menu including White Truffle, Black Truffle and White Asparagus! Free Corkage!', 'Salmon Confit, Fresh Blue Crabmeat Gratin on White Asparagus, Slow Cooked US Prime Beef Tenderloin', '', 'You can enjoy the French cuisine in Chef Studio by Eddy tucked away in an industrial building in Aberdeen. Chef Eddy Leung designs and presents you the most stunning eight course seasonal tasting menu of “real food & real flavours” with different seasonal luxury ingredients including black truffle, white truffle and white asparagus. 
Free Corkage! Bring your own wine and enjoy the meal!', '2-min walk from Bus Station - Nam Long Shan Road', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2311, 'en_US', 'Gainmore Cuisine', 'Michelin recommended restaurant, you can enjoy the chicken hotpot with a secret family recipe.', 'Abalone Mixed Mushroom Lo Mein, Gainmore Chicken Pot, Gainmore Rice Noodles, Abalone Chicken Pot', '', 'It\'s all about Yunnan Cross Bridge rice noodles at lunch and chicken hotpot for dinner at this simple and clean two storey restaurant with tasty hotpot uses a secret family recipe supplemented by Chinese herbs and condiments. Lovers of spicier food can opt for the Sichuan hotpot which is available with differing levels of heat with speciality is the chicken hotpot with abalone.
', '2-min walk from Mini Bus Station Lion Rock Road', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2313, 'en_US', 'Sai Kung Sing Kee', 'Michelin 1 star seafood restaurant in Sai Kung, you will know what\'s the true seafood in Sing Kee!', 'Steamed Scallop and Vermicelli with Sake, Salt and Pepper Abalone, Salt and Pepper Baked Crab, Cripsy Chicken, Cuttlefish Cake, Traditional Abalone, Honey Sparerib', '', 'Sing Kee seafood restaurant has been awarded a Michelin star in the new edition of the Michelin Guide Hong Kong Macau 2014, 2015. The three-storey restaurant with 12 dining rooms is located in the large red building near the old-town car park. It was rated as “a very good restaurant in its category” with cuisine prepared to a consistently high standard. Standout dishes include the crispy chicken and the abalone menu.
', 'MTR Hang Hau Station, change 101M mini bus', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2314, 'en_US', 'Van Gogh Kitchen', 'Private Italian kitchen with the theme of Van Gogh', 'Foie Gras, 98% Mushroom Cream Soup, Chocolate Molten Lava Cake', '', 'The choice for nobles, the essence of continental Italian dishes
At the bustling Hennessy Road of Causeway Bay, there is renowned Italian restaurant which has been run for over 7 years on the  fifth floor of an old residential building.
Once you get into the restaurant, you can see an English snooker table and the exquisite restaurant design with red wall. All these designs match with the masterpiece of Van Gogh - Night Cafe. Not only the Night Cafe, there are some other works of Van Gogh being displayed in the cafe, for instance Cafe Terrace at Night, The Bedroom at Arles as well as The Starry Night. Those imitations are still presented their essence which makes the restaurant is filled with arts.
\n\nHow to enjoy birthday promo at this restaurant
1. Book a table on your birthday (min. 2 people), and choose birthday as dining purpose.
2. Show up at the restaurant on the day of dining and show your ID to restaurant staff for verification.
3. Enjoy your birthday meal and don\'t forget to pay with EZTABLE!
4. You will receive your birthday gift in form of coupon code, two days after your dining! 
5. The amount of coupon is equal to your total dining amount divided by total diners, with maximum of HKD 500. 
6. Coupon code will be valid for your next dining at any restaurants with Checkout service and is valid for 30 days.', '5 -min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit B', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2348, 'en_US', 'Kin\'s Kitchen', 'Michelin 1 star Chinese restaurant managed by the celebrity chef - Lau Chun', 'Kin\'s Smoked Chicken, Pigeon Slow Cooked in Shaoxing Wine Sause, Pan, fried Sweet Corn with Soya Sause', '', 'Kin\'s Kitchen started in 2004, featuring traditional Cantonese dishes by art, culture & food critic LAU Kin Wai and LAU Chun.
Kin\'s Kitchen has always insisted on the traditional Cantonese food cooked without MSG. The smoked chicken is the signature dish and is well reputed. In 2011, Kin’s Kitchen won a Michelin Star and was one of the few traditional Cantonese restaurants to do so. The father and son duo have also designed menus for Cathay Pacific First Class, and Guest Chef appearances at The American Club in HK.
Kin\'s Kitchen has always insisted on the best methods and ingredients for their Cantonese food, for example, salt-baked chicken is really cooked in the traditional way, rather than using short cuts. The salt is ground, then the chicken is oven baked and cooked.
Modern equipment, new skills and a new menu with more dishes, such as using the Sous Vide technique cook pigeon at 70 degrees with Chinese ingredients for marination.
The other special twist at Kin’s Kitchen is the menu featuring over 10 different dishes of chicken cook traditional recipes. Using “full term” chickens that are matured to over 100 days, Kin’s Kitchen will not be chickens treated with fast-growth homones.
', '8 -min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit A', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2353, 'en_US', 'Namo Avant Thai', 'Enjoy the Victoria Harbour View with AVANT THAI cuisine', 'Red Prawn Tom Yum, T.A.J Beef Steak, \"X.L.O.\" Giant Atlantic Octopus', '', 'NAMO is a ‘must try’ culinary destination with a stunning view of Victoria Harbour located in Empire Centre, Tsim Sha Tsui East. Launched by renowned Thai chef Khun Wijannarongk Kunchit (whose expertise stems from working with the likes of Thai royals, dignitaries, and celebrity chef Bobby Chinn) together with Michelin Star chef Alejandro Sanchez. Namo is not a ‘contemporary Thai’ restaurant nor is it ‘fusion’ Thai food … it is the NEW Thai cuisine…  A NEW direction for Thai food – incorporating the traditional, tried and trusted recipes of this most delicate of Asian cuisines and infusing them with modern cooking methods and preparation styles and using the premium ingredients available to our Master-chefs today.', '6-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit P1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2354, 'en_US', 'He Jiang', 'Don\'t miss the Sichuan and Huaiyang cuisines in He Jiang!', 'La Zui Chicken, Sichuan Style Roasted Duck, Grandma Style Braised Pork in Soy', '', 'He Jiang features a new blend of Sichuan and Huaiyang cuisines, two major schools of Chinese cooking and gathers the most sought-after delicacies in one menu. New creations as well as authentic specialties best exemplify the essences of the flavors and ingredients in plenty.
If all tables available online are fully allocated now although there may still be tables at the restaurant.', '13-min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit A', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2356, 'en_US', 'Nanhai No.1', 'Take a culinary voyage around the South China Sea', 'King Prawn served in Bang Sause with Fried Mantou, Crispy and Steamed Rice servied in Lobster Consomme, Pan, fried Black Pork with Soy', '', 'Nanhai No. 1 combines contemporary Chinese cuisine, cutting-edge interior design and famous city panoramas.
Named after pioneering Chinese naval explorer Zheng He\'s 15th- century \'treasure fleet\' nanhai no.1 is envisioned as a culinary voyage of exploration inspired by the sea.
Daily fresh seafood caught in the South China Sea is the star attraction of the restaurant and the seafood is prepared in a variety of culinary expressions - ranging from roasted, steamed and sautéed to baked, stir- fired, pan-fired or grilled.
* Window seat (1st and 2nd road table by the window) at HKD 500 per person minimum charge, other seating no minimum charge.
* If all tables available online are fully allocated now although there may still be tables at the restaurant.', '9-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit H', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2357, 'en_US', 'QUEMO', 'Enjoy the Paellas in this Rare Spanish/Mediterranean restaurant in town!', 'Meat Pork Ribs and Iberico Chorizo Paella, Sauteed Mussels with Garlic Chili and White Wine, Roasted Suckling Pig from Avila', '', 'QUEMO, commonly heard in restaurants and kitchens in Spain, literally means \"I\'m burning\". The element of fire heats things up at Quemo which features paellas and barbacoa, a style of Spanish barbecue. 
Buzzing with energy, QUEMO serves exceptional food and drinks in a convivial atmosphere, that will bring smiles and surprises
QUEMO features a modern rustic dining room, a tapas bar, a spacious outdoor terrace, and a private dining / wine tasting room.
* If all tables available online are fully allocated now although there may still be tables at the restaurant.', '7-min walk from MTR Wan Chai station Exit A3', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2358, 'en_US', 'Yè Shanghai (Kowloon)', 'Michelin 1 star Shanghai Restaurant located in Marco Polo Hotel', 'Braised Prawns with Onion in Sweet Chili Sause, Steamed Pork Belly Wrapped with Fragrant Leaves, Whole Roasted Duck', '', 'Art Deco inspirations and an inviting modern ambience, yè shanghai Kowloon (the name means \"Shanghai Nights\") celebrates Shanghai in it’s heyday, when it was known as the Paris of the East ... the spirit of old Shanghai lives on.
At yè shanghai, our chefs recreate the tastes of the celebrated dishes that will always be Shanghai. Every dish is prepared with a touch of innovation for your pleasure, while dining in the intimate setting inspired by the chic era of old Shanghai.
yè shanghai Kowloon has been awarded Michelin stars since 2010
If all tables available online are fully allocated now although there may still be tables at the restaurant.', '9 -min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L6', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2359, 'en_US', 'Yè  Shanghai (Hong Kong)', 'Michelin 1 star Shanghai Restaurant located in Pacific Place', 'Braised Prawns with Onion in Sweet Chili Sause, Steamed Pork Belly Wrapped with Fragrant Leaves, Whole Turbot Fish Frilled in Charcoal Oven', '', 'The Metropolis of Shanghai, a jewel of style and culture, is renowned for the cuisines of its surrounding provinces, Jiangsu and Zhejiang, each representing a famous regional cooking of China. Hearty and diverse cooking techniques that emphasize braising, roasting, quick-frying and steaming result in dishes that are well-developed and balanced in flavor notes.
At yè shanghai, our chefs recreate the tastes of the celebrated dishes that will always be Shanghai. Every dish is prepared with a touch of innovation for your pleasure, while dining in the intimate setting inspired by the chic era of old Shanghai.
yè shanghai  Hong Kong is located in Pacific Place, Queensway, a leading shopping centre specialising in high-end retail, dining and accommodation.
If all tables available online are fully allocated now although there may still be tables at the restaurant.', '5 -min walk from MTR Admiralty station Exit C1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2414, 'en_US', 'The Boss', 'Michelin 1 star Chinese restaurant - \"The Boss\" uses only the best quality and the freshest ingredients including wagyu beef and black truffles, specially air-flown in to ensure optimal freshness.', 'Braised Abalone with Goose Web, Pan Fried Scallop with Homemade Sauce, Braised Garoupa with Homemade Sauce & Garlic in Casserole', '', 'On the main street in Central, and be unwrapped in the modern-luxe décor of \"The Boss\", while tucking in to some of the most classic of signature dishes, that will certainly keep you coming back for more. \"The Boss\" uses only the best quality and the freshest ingredients in each and every of our exquisitely crafted dishes, including our premium selection of choice wagyu beef and black truffles, specially air-flown in to ensure optimal freshness.', '4 -min walk fromMTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2425, 'en_US', 'The Food Gallery - The Langham Hotel', 'Enjoy lobster and fresh oyster international buffet in The Langham Hotel', 'Lobster, Oyster', '', 'Boasting a fresh, modern ambience, guests will delight in the extensive selection of international seafood, fresh salads, interactive cooking stations, delectable desserts and much more. Active and vibrant kitchens in full view with a delightful blend of highly creative and authentic Chinese, Asian and Western fare influenced from Hong Kong’s diverse world-class cuisines.', '7-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2427, 'en_US', 'T\'ang  Court- The Langham Hotel', 'Michelin 2 star Chinese restaurant in The Langham Hotel, you must try the award wining Dishes!', 'Stir, Fried Fresh Lobster with Spring Onion Red Onion and Shallots, Sautéed Prawns and Crab Roe with Golden, Fried Pork and Crab Meat Puffs, Sautéed Prawns with Asparagus with Deep, Fried Taro Puffs Filled with Shrimp', '', 'Michelin two-star restaurant - T\'ang Court reflects the classic timelessness of the Tang Dynasty, China\'s golden age. Amid lavish furnishings, dine on authentic Cantonese culinary masterpieces in this legendary Hong Kong restaurant.
US Food and Wine Magazine includes T\'ang Court on its \"Go list 2008\".
US Hotels Magazine named T\'ang Court one of the world\'s Top Ten Hotel Restaurants and the restaurant received a Gold with Distinction Medal in The Best of the Best Culinary Awards organized by the Hong Kong Tourism Board two years in a row.
Travel & Leisure has listed T\'ang Court as one of only ten restaurants worldwide on its annual Hot List of the World\'s 100 Fabulous Places and Things.
T’ang Court’s Braised Garoupa Head and Brisket with Roasted Pork / Sliced Garoupa with Deer tendons has recently been awarded the 2013 Best of the Best Culinary Awards – Gold with Distinction Award - for the category of Signature Seafood (Fish in Two Styles).', '7-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2428, 'en_US', 'Palm Court - The Langham Hotel', 'Experience the British lifestyle in The Langham Hotel, must try the Afternoon Tea with Wedgwood!', 'Afternoon Tea with Wedgwood, Palm Court Valrhona Chocolate, Traditional Langham Breakfast', '', 'Palm Court is a fresh and elegant space that serves as a dramatic backdrop to the lobby, featuring natural stone flooring and painted timber columns that showcase a traditional yet luxurious finish. Restyled after its namesake at The Langham, London where traditional English afternoon tea was served over 140 years ago, Palm Court pays tribute to its heritage with a bespoke version of the tradition – “The Langham Afternoon Tea with Wedgwood” – serving Wedgwood specialty teas in tailor-made “Langham Rose” Wedgwood tea ware with a special menu created by our Executive Pastry Chef. Elevating the experience with delicate confections and savoury pleasures, the world of Wedgwood comes to the Langham, Hong Kong. 
For those who wish to take away signature sweets for family, friends or co-workers, Palm Court offers the perfect palatable present. Enjoy homemade treats including éclairs, sacher torte, cakes and other gourmet delights to celebrate any occasion or just because. Every attention to detail from each ingredient to thoughtful packaging, showcases the labour of love that was made special for our guests. Give the gift of pastry perfection.
The Langham Afternoon Tea with Wedgwood” – serving Wedgwood specialty teas in tailor-made “Langham Rose” Wedgwood tea ware with a special menu created by our Executive Pastry Chef. Elevating the experience with delicate confections and savoury pleasures, the world of Wedgwood comes to the Langham, Hong Kong.', '7-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2429, 'en_US', 'Main St. Dell - The Langham Hotel', 'Traditional New York style cuisine in The Langham Hotel, prepare your camera and don\'t miss the 12oz Monster Beef Burger!', '12oz Monster Beef Burger, Canda Rib Eye Steak, Brooklyn Salad, Lobster Omelette', '', 'Taste a slice of The Big Apple at Main St. Deli. In the true spirit of New York, Main St. Deli opened in April 2001 as Hong Kong\'s first authentic New York style deli. The outlet offers New York deli favourites, such as Reuben sandwiches, pastrami on rye, hot corned beef, brisket, knishes, bagels, salads and chicken soup with matzoh balls.', '7-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2463, 'en_US', 'Gitone Limited', 'Shanghai cuisine private kitchen, food serve with artistic decor', 'Fried Spotted Crab with Green Soy Bean, Stewed Pork Trotters in Brown Sauce, Mushroom Roll with Jin Hua Ham Mash and Zucchini', '', 'Gitone is evolved from Gitone Fine Arts started in 1995. Its scope of operation is threefold. It serves as a gallery for art display and sale. Primarily it carries its own art collection and the art works of Mr. Terence Lee, renowned Hong Kong painter and ceramic artist. As an art workshop it provides comprehensive painting and ceramics classes for adults and children. In the evening it provides exquisite cuisine for private fine dining.
Relocated to the Soho East area in March 2008, it progresses to reach out and extend to a wider public. The elegantly decorated new premises on the waterfront opposite a park provides an excellent setting and congenial environment for enjoyment of art and dining.
Art stems from living Dining encompasses the joy of sharing. With this belief, Gitone fuses the two together in a humble wish to add some colours to life.', '5-min walk from  MTR Sai Wan Ho station Exit B', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2481, 'en_US', 'Anthony\'s Ranch', 'Traditional American Taxes style cuisine, don\'t miss the Grilled/Smoke steak!', 'Grilled/Smoked Steak, Grilled/Smoked Chicken and Lamb, Prime Steak, Prime Lamb Chop', '', 'Anthony’s Ranch is dedicated to delivering top quality “Real Texas Smoke House” foods to the Sai Kung Area. We use Apple, Pear, Maple and Oak wood in our smoking process. Anthony’s imports Chilled Harris Ranch (California) Prime Steaks all cooked on our American Char Rock Broiler.
At Anthony’s we grind our US hamburger for the day, Roast/Smoke all our own meats, and make all our own accompaniments in house.', 'MTR Hang Hau Station, change 101M mini bus', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2498, 'en_US', 'Koh Thai Restaurant (Mid Level, Central)', 'The traditional Thai cuisine in Central, you can sit at the outdoor and enjoy the view of mid-level Central', 'Coconut Seafood Curry Rice, Tom Yum Kung, Pad Thai', '', 'With the claim of being the highest restaurant on the world’s longest 
escalator our restaurant in Mid-Levels is a true gem for both locals and tourists alike. Split on two levels with a leafy, peaceful roof-garden overlooking the impressive Mosque and gardens, this is the perfect venue to while away your time and relax while enjoying our exquisite Koh Thai food and hospitality.', '6-min walk from MTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2519, 'en_US', 'SPOON by Alain Ducasse - InterContinental Hong Kong', 'Enjoy the Michelin 2 stars French cuisine in SPOON by Alain Ducasse with the most stunning Victoria Harbour View!', 'Thick medallion of Veal with baby carrots parsley and capers, Chocolate From Our Factory in Paris with Crunchy Praline, Sunday Brunch', '', 'With its contemporary French cuisine and stunning harbour views, the 1-Michelin star SPOON by Alain Ducasse is one of Hong Kong and Asia\'s most sought-after dining experiences.  SPOON showcases a seductive menu and wine list --- all with French nuances inspired by world famous chef Alain Ducasse.
Designed by Tony Chi, SPOON has a contemporary décor with subdued earth tones. Of particular note is the ceiling, which is adorned with 550 hand-blown Murano mercury glass spoons. A unique blend of textures are incorporated into the décor with a rust-coloured leather Bar, modern French provincial chairs covered in eel skin fabric at the SPOON Bar and real mink cushions adorning the banquettes.
The SPOON Private Dining Room offers an ideal setting for dinner parties for up to 14 guests. SPOON’s exclusive Chef’s Table, with its bird’s eye view of the open kitchen in action, provides the ultimate in private dining for up to 6 guests --- with a tailor-made menu created and presented personally by SPOON Executive Chef Stephane Gortina.', '3-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit J', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2558, 'en_US', 'G Cuisine', 'Chef Lau has been creating cuisine for over 20 years in 5 stars hotel, enjoy 5 stars hotel food in this local place.', 'Foie Gras, Pan Seared Scallop with Crab Roe Salad, Seafood Pasta', '(Last order at 22:00)', 'Fabulous food is only one aspect of your dining experience at G.Gallery & G.Cuisine. We have a carefully selected ingredient to appeal to every palate. Executive Chef Pino\'s New Italian menu draws from Asian Modern and global influences, which mingle seamlessly in a skillfully straightforward presentation of flavors. Utilizing Local\'s farmer\'s markets for seasonal inspiration , Chef Pino carefully crafts his menus, which change daily. In addition to a full dinner menu, a tasting menu are also available.', '2 -min walk from MTR Lai Chi Kok station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2559, 'en_US', 'G Gallery', 'Located in an industrial building, great for catching up with friends', 'Italian Appetizer Platter, Grill Lamb Chop, Miso Marinated Black Cod Fillet and Clam with Sea Urchin Sake Butter Sauce', '(Last order at 22:00)', 'Fabulous food is only one aspect of your dining experience at G.Gallery & G.Cuisine. We have a carefully selected ingredient to appeal to every palate. Executive Chef Pino\'s New Italian menu draws from Asian Modern and global influences, which mingle seamlessly in a skillfully straightforward presentation of flavors. Utilizing Local\'s farmer\'s markets for seasonal inspiration , Chef Pino carefully crafts his menus, which change daily. In addition to a full dinner menu, a tasting menu are also available.', '2 -min walk from MTR Lai Chi Kok station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2588, 'en_US', 'Small Potato (Sun Wui Road)', 'Lazy cozy cafe in Causeway Bay for you and your friends', 'Quebec Poutine with Honey BBQ Pork Ribs, Stuffing Eggplant with Beef & Cheese, Deep Fried Prawn with Sweet Chili and Sauver Sauce', '', 'Small Potato is the perfect place of getting yourself a break. With quality service, couches and sofa chairs, cheerful music and soft lighting, all we want is to bring you a sweet, cheerful and homey environment. And that\'s what we are here for.\n\nJust as we always believe that home is the best place to indulge ourselves, Small Potato is undoubtedly the second best. And we try our very best to convince you with that too. For those who come for the first time in, their gaze will be immediately transfixed by the mega-size Foosball Table. Here you\'re invited to experience how fabulously simple it could be to indulge yourself. For those who are looking for excitements, the Foosball Table, TV Games, Card Games and Comics are all ready to wash your stress away. If you just want to soothe your mind and have a chatty, friendly gathering, you and your gang may simply throw yourselves into the fluffy couches and enjoy your delicious refreshments', '3 -min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit A', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2379, 'en_US', 'Sushi Shikon', 'Omakase sushi restaurant, Michelin 3 star Japanese restaurant', 'Omakase', '', 'Awarded three Michelin stars in the 2014 and 2015 Hong Kong/Macau Michelin Guide, Sushi Shikon is the quintessential Ginza sushi experience, now available in Hong Kong. Sushi Shikon is the first branch of Sushi Yoshitake in Ginza, founded by Master Chef Masahiro Yoshitake, which has held three Michelin stars in Tokyo since 2012. Each day, the finest fresh ingredients are flown to Hong Kong live from Tokyo’s famous Tsukiji market, and extraordinary lengths have been taken to provide not just world-class Japanese cuisine, but also a complete cultural experience. The restaurant is overseen by executive chef Yoshiharu Kakinuma, who worked with Chef Yoshitake in Tokyo for several years before taking over Sushi Shikon in Hong Kong and achieving the 3 michelin stars for Hong Kong. Dining at Sushi Shikon is an unforgettable experience, served in an intimate atmosphere, where guests interact with and observe the master chefs craft each dish over the course of a two-hour meal from just across a beautiful, 8-seat wooden Hinoki counter.
', '3 -min walk from MTR Sheung Wan station Exit A2', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2557, 'en_US', 'TT Party Party Restaurant', 'City garden hidden in busy city, enjoy the European fusion cuisine here!', 'Tomato Soup in Whole Tomato, Wild Mushroom with Black Truffle Sauce, Roasted Lamb Rack with Pommery Mustard Sauce, Roasted Spring Chicken with Lemon Butter Sauce', '', 'TT Party Party Restaurant in Tsim Sha Tsui is the signature European fusion restaurant. The restaurant enriches with an extraordinary, warm and friendly dining experience with courteous and attentive service in an exquisite and serene hideaway at the heart of our hectic city. We also offer different dining function styles which tailormake to your needs.', '8 -min walk from MTR Jordan station Exit D', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2589, 'en_US', 'Le Port Parfume', 'Great French seafood restaurant for friends union in Central.', 'Slow Cook Pork Cheek, Griled US Prime Rib Eye, Blue Cheese Gelato & Honey Comb', '', 'At Le Port Parfumé we are dedicated to serving the freshest wild-caught seafood sourced directly from local fishermen who harvest the bounty of the sea from the cool depths of the waters around Hong Kong. Prepared with flair and imagination, our classic yet creative dishes will delight and refresh your palate while paying homage to our twin sources of inspiration, Hong Kong and France.
Our name is French for Fragrant Harbour, the original meaning of Hong Kong, chosen to reflect the crisp, natural marine flavours and aromas inherent in the seafood we present. A refreshing simple menu is redrawn daily on a chalkboard representing our inspired take on the day\'s best produce.', '8 -min walk from MTR Sheung Wan station Exit E2', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2017, 'en_US', 'The Harbourview - Harbour Restaurant', 'Offering a captivating view of the harbour, features a vast selection of international dining with buffet and a la carte dining', 'Oyster, Foie gras, Movenpick icecream', '', 'Recently redecorated, The Harbour Restaurant lends a fashionable yet graceful flavour when a blend of different natural wood hues matches with deep colour carpet and a substantial use of glass panels. The restaurant serves splendid breakfast, lunch and dinner buffets in addition to a specially-picked a la carte menu, promises to please delight every single palate.', '12-min walk from MTR Wan Chai station Exit A1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2146, 'en_US', 'La Maison de l\' Orient - Dorsett Kwun Tong', 'Enjoy the healthy Chinese food in La Maison de l\' Orient', 'Grilled Tiger Prawns with Thyme, Chinese Style BBQ Ribs, Golden Stuffed Crab Shell, Black Truffle Shrimp with Fu Yong Sauce, Signature Rose Liquor Marinated Chicken', '', 'For food connoisseurs, the 4-star Dorsett Kwun Tong, Hong Kong\'s Chinese restaurant, La Maison de l\' Orient, offers the ultimate dining option with its presentation of luxurious Chinese dishes complemented by a pleasing ambience to heighten one\'s dining experience.La Maison de l\' Orient use the fresh ingredients and healthy cooking style, you can\'t eat with low sodium, low oil, low sugar and without MSG here!', '8-min walk from  MTR Kwun Tong station Exit B2', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2258, 'en_US', 'The Herbivores - Soho', 'Vegetarian food that will stun you taste bug', 'Mash & Cheese, Mango Risotto, Herbivores Bomb', '', 'Like the people of Soho, we are an adventurous bunch and thrive on crafting and improving recipes, never letting ourselves be boring.Herbivores is staffed by a young, talented, and dedicated group of energetic employees who truly appreciate the vision of vegetarianism. Coupled with enthusiasm to work with vegetarian food, our goal is to introduce creative vegetarian cooking that will make you gobsmacked!
With an interior of pale wood, exposed brick, communal seating and chalk-scrawled blackboards displaying colorful facts about vegetarianism, The Herbivores certainly looks the eco part, and a long and varied menu offering ensures that it taste as good as it looks.
', '9  -min walk from MTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2301, 'en_US', 'G7 Private Kitchen', 'Romantic Italian Private Kitchen in Central', 'Caviar Angel Hair, US Prime Rib & Bone Marrow', '', 'G7 Private Dining is an elegant oasis in the Hong Kong dining scene. Tucked away in a discreet yet central location just above Wyndham Street, G7 provides clients with the perfect intimate setting for group dinners, parties, special occasions, or just a romantic dinner for two.
Chef Eddy is well known in Hong Kong\'s dining circle as a pioneer of the private kitchen scene since the 1990\'s, and with G7 he is back in Central to share his authentic and refined take on Italian food. Using only the freshest seasonal produce, from Chef Eddy\'s home-made breads and pastas, to white truffles from Alba and fresh daily seafood from Hokkaido, G7 provides clients with a culinary experience not to be missed! Our open kitchen and private room also provides you the choice of immersing yourself in the passion of the day\'s cooking or relaxing in privacy and enjoying Chef Eddy and the team\'s cooking talents. Free Corkage!', '6 -min walk MTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2312, 'en_US', 'SYUT', 'A combination of music, cuisine, design theme restaurant created by Hong Kong instrumental band tfvsjs', 'Carbonara, Malt Pumpkin Orzo', 'Closed on Sunday', 'SYUT is a cafe founded by Hong Kong instrumental band tfvsjs. The cafe locates at a lofty industrial venue at Tai Yip Street. The multi function space facilitates not only eatery, but also a recording studio, boutique drum shop Battle Stage and tfvsjs’s rehearsal studio. For the past few years tfvsjs is fortunate enough to share our passion in music, and now we are taking a step further to demonstrate our professions in cookery, dining, design and motion picture production. With our aim to foster a cultural exchange platform for Kwun Tong district, a series of design forum, independent movie screenings and musician master class will be held in the near future. Please stay tune to our Facebook page update.', '2 -min walk from MTR Ngau Tau Kok station Exit B4', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2338, 'en_US', 'RA Restaurant & Lounge', 'Named after the ancient Egyptian Sun God, RA-Restaurant and Lounge is located along the bustling stretch of sea front bars and restaurants in Tsim Shat Tsui East', 'RA’s Signature Middle Eastern Mixed Grill Platter, Hummus Sauce, Lamb Kofta', 'Belly Dancer\nMonday – Saturday:  20:30 onwards\nHappy Hours\n16:00 - 20:00', 'Named after the ancient Egyptian Sun God, RA – Restaurant and Lounge is located along the bustling stretch of sea front bars and restaurants in Tsim Shat Tsui East
RA redefines alfresco dining with stunning harbor views, inspired interiors and its innovative fusion of Moroccan cuisine along with exotic belly dancer shows daily.
RA presents three dynamic dining and lounging spaces. The indoor dining area is a dimly lit sitting surrounded by contemporary Egyptian stone carvings. The Private room – styled like a Moroccan den, is designed for intimate meals and private functions. The outdoor – a spacious seated area where guests can indulge in cool cocktails and fruit flavored Shishas /Hookahs (Egyptian water pipe) while taking in uninterrupted harbor views.
