(2417, 'en_US', 'Bar Umami - Le Méridien Cyberport', 'Fresh sushi and sashimi served in Le Méridien', 'Hand Rolled Sushi, Sacchi Martini, Crab', '', 'Chic and stylish designs are juxtaposed with exquisite international gastronomic specialties to make Le Méridien Cyberport a timeless venue for indulging any craving.Our chic sushi bar offers unique tamaki and sushi in an outdoor setting and romantic dining area. Its cocktail bar has preparations for an astonishing variety of imaginative cocktails – including the saketini – to enjoy in the terraced garden.', 'Bus Station - Cyberport Road', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2418, 'en_US', 'Nam Fong - Le Méridien Cyberport', 'Traditional fine dinning Chinese restaurant in Le Méridien Cyberport', 'Stuffed Crab Shell, Pan Fried Shrimp, Steam Grouper Fish, Abalone with Osyter Sauce, Chicken Fried Rice with Truffle', '', 'The stunningly designed, high-ceilinged Nam Fong is a modern Chinese restaurant serving superb Cantonese specialties and top quality fresh Dim Sum with a millennium twist. The chic décor looks toward the future even as it subtly nods to nineteen-sixties design in woodwork or furniture shapes—a perfect backdrop to the newly re-envisioned traditional fare. Serving lunch and dinner. Adjoining the main dining area is the Le Méridien Ballroom, fitted with the latest audio-visual equipment for events and celebrations.', 'Bus Station - Cyberport Road', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2423, 'en_US', 'The Bostonian - The Langham Hotel', 'Offer seafood menu for lunch and dinner; Sunday offers seafood buffet', 'Duck Leg Confit Spring Rolln with Ginger Sauce, Boston Lobster, Charco Grilled Tiger Prawns with Lobster Butter, American Angus Tenderloin, Mint Crusted Welsh Rack of Lamb with White Asparagus', '', 'This well-established American restaurant has long been a Hong Kong favourite and is recommended by Michelin Guide.
The Bostonian has an excellent reputation for its lively atmosphere and superb dishes such as Boston lobsters served American style. Expect serious American-sized portions too. And our sommelier also has much to offer.', '7-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit L5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2438, 'en_US', 'Loong Yuen - Holiday Inn Golden Mile', 'Loong Yuen Cantonese Restaurant combines the traditional and modern characteristics of Chinese Restaurant, it provides authentic Cantonese cuisine', 'Shrimp Fried Rice with Shrimp Sauce, Abalone with Oyster Sauce, Drunken Shrimp (Shrimp Marianted with Wine)', '', 'The award winning Loong Yuen Cantonese Restaurant is the perfect place to experience top quality Cantonese fare and the restaurant is voted as one of the Hong Kong\'s Best Restaurants by Hong Kong Tatler. Its extensive menu of luscious Chinese dim sum and innovative Cantonese dishes will surely enchant your gastronomical experience.', '5 -min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit N5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2439, 'en_US', 'Bistro on the Mile - Holiday Inn Golden Mile', 'Features a wide selection of local fares and it is well known with its international buffet', 'Ice Cream, Dessert, Salmon Sashimi, Osyter', '', 'Bistro on the Mile overlooks the hustle bustle of Nathan Road which offers all day dining in a relaxed ambience. It features a wide selection of local fares and it is well known with its international buffet.Take your date for an all-you-can-eat international dinner buffet at Bistro on the Mile. A generous selection of seafood, desserts and sashmi.', '5-min walk from MTR East Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit N5', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2493, 'en_US', 'SHIKA Teppan-Yaki & Sushi', 'Enjoy the Omakase sushi and teppanyaki in SHIKA!', 'Fig Tempura, Foie Gras, A5 Wagyu', '', 'Designed by APU in 2014, Teppan-Yaki & Sushi is a stylish modern Japanese Teppan-yaki restaurant located in Causeway Bay. Prior to entering the main dining area on the second floor, hungry diners will be led by a long and inviting stairway with raw cement walls. On entering the 2,700 sq.ft restaurant, a stunning sushi bar underneath the hanging filament bulbs presents its signature dishes. Unlike other Japanese restaurants, this project is characterized by colorful hexagon tiles, wooden floor, and the widely used wood and concrete materials. The design also identify the importance of privacy, therefore three VIP rooms are built to cater for luncheons and other private dining occasions. Further, the wallpaper bears traditional Japanese paintings, offering an unique, exotic dinning experience.
