(2595, 'en_US', 'L\'altro', 'The prestigious two-starred Michelin chef Philippe Leveille is opening a new Italian eatery in Central\'s L.place', 'Grilled Pigeon with Squid and Chorizo Brunoise, Homemade Spaghetti with Clams and Pantelleria Capers, Gelato', '', 'Simply named L’altro which means “the other”, the new restaurant aims to create a unique identity and ambience different to other restaurants and bring an extraordinary dining experience. It is also looking to take Hong Kong’s food industry to a new high by serving up heavenly authentic Italian fare infused with the best French culinary techniques.
The classy restaurant interior is furnished to the highest standard in cold tones of grey and white with the harmonic combination of Italian elements such as marble, reflective mirrors and Murano glass. The dining area is understated and uncomplicated and features a custom design stainless steel display shelf. The display shelf houses an extensive glass window with stripe pattern through to the kitchen, where guests may enjoy the chefs’ silhouette within.
With seating capacity of 64, the restaurant has two private function rooms which can be used separately or adjoined together and accommodating up to 16 people at a time. It has also incorporated a bar area to seat 6 customers with an extensive wine library to house a wide range of wines meticulously selected by the sommelier.', '5 -min walk from MTR Sheung Wan station Exit E2', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2596, 'en_US', 'JAR', 'Spanish restaurant located in Central, enjoy tapas and wine', 'Spanish Paella with King Prawns, Crab Cake, Banoffee Pie', '', 'JAR’s food is best described as contemporary comfort food, following the bistro ethos of simple approach and robust flavors. Our menu is created with lots of enthusiasm and changes seasonally.
“Comfortable, convivial and unpretentious, JAR is a welcome addition to urban Central. It is the neighborhood restaurant we all wish we lived or worked around the corner from – comfy banquettes, smart clientele, pure and enthusiastic menu, and friendly staff. It’s like finding yourself in a little den of comforting food, balance and harmony.”', '5 -min walk from MTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2598, 'en_US', 'ATUM Desserant', 'Artistic, improvisation dessert created just for you', 'Improvisation', '', 'ATUM desserant, formed by two young entrepreneurs, is a dessert restaurant with rich imagination and contemporary presentation. You must try the most popular item “Improvisation”, the Chef in ATUM will use different dessert ingredient to present you a total experience of “Improvisation”. You can find many elements e.g. liquid nitrogen ice cream, mousse cake, freeze dried fruit and sauce etc..', '2 -min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit C', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2599, 'en_US', 'Friendmily', 'Famous chef cook with unique style, excellent food with reasonable price', 'American Style Roasted Ribs, King Crab, Black Truffle Seafood Risotto', '', 'The best place to dine with your friends & family – Friendmily.
Located in an industrial building in Kwun Tong serving unique western dishes and wine. There is no fancy decoration but a warm and cozy environment which make you feel relax. Just come and spend your perfect time here!', '4-min walk from  MTR Kwun Tong station Exit A2', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2603, 'en_US', 'Number Fifteen', 'White walls coupled with wooden tables and chairs, there is a feeling of a foreign cafe. Great spot for reunion', 'Steak Rack, Black Truffle Pasta, Spanish Style Pork', '', 'We are a restaurant located at the heart of Hong Kong\'s hectic yet humble industrial area, serving up modern British cuisine with a twist. We offer great, relaxed atmosphere and more importantly, great food that would appeal to everyone (we hope so anyway). It\'s a place for those who aspire to high-end eatery standards but without the formality.
