(2605, 'en_US', 'Tak Lung Restaurant', 'Best of the Best Culinary Awards (2014)', 'Tai Yeh Chicken, Duck Feet Wrap, Sweet and Sour Pork', '', 'Tak Lung Restaurant has stood firm in San Po Kong for 40 years, serving ancient Chinese cuisine. Even though they serve traditional Cantonese dishes, most Hongkongers will be surprised by unusual plates such as Tai Yeh Chicken, which is smoked with pu-erh tea and cane sugar, or fish intestines baked with eggs. Menus are in Chinese only.', 'Bus Station - Yi Lun Street', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2606, 'en_US', 'Tequila on Davis', 'Tequila on Davis is an authentic, casual and friendly Mexican restaurant and bar.', 'Quesadillas with Chicken, Nachos', '', 'Tequila on Davis is an authentic, casual and friendly Mexican restaurant and bar. Situated in the heart of the burgeoning bar district of Davis Street, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong, Tequila on Davis serves delicious Mexican food and a wide range of specialty Tequila.
\'Tequila Upstairs\'  first floor area is perfect for private parties and events, with a full range of audio visual equipment for any occasion. It is also a good place to hang out for Brunch on weekends.', '3 -min walk from MTR Kennedy Town station Exit C', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3249, 'en_US', 'Top Floor Bar & Grill', 'Restaurant Chef had over 30 years of experience in kitchen and worked for several five-star hotels before.', 'Alaska Crab Cake, Chicken Tikka, Fresh Oyster, King Prawns with Spaghetti', 'Closed on Sunday', 'Top floor Bar & Grill is located in the heart of Tsim Sha Tsui. It is an international restaurants serving different countries cuisine. You can find outdoor seat and there are 2 VIP rooms for any occasions. The executive chef have over 30 years’ experience and he has worked in 5 star hotel and steakhouse. .', '5 -min walk from MTR Tsim Shai Tsui station Exit A1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3253, 'en_US', 'BV Kitchen', 'Must try burger pocket list! You can\'t miss the foie gras burger!', 'Foie Gras Black Augus Burger, Live Boston Lobster & Portabello Burger With Black Truffle Cheese Sauce', '', 'BV Kitchen is located in Tsim Sha Tusi. This place is suitable for gathering, party, and friend reunion etc. You must try the Classic Burger here with different combination e.g. bacon, cheese, onion etc. For more luxury choices, you can enjoy the wagyu patty and foie gras! Don’t miss it and enjoy your meal in BV Kitchen..', '7-min walk from MTR Jordan Station Exit D', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3254, 'en_US', 'Inakaya', 'Inakaya, as the traditional ‘Robata-yaki’ restaurant, has been loved by substantial numbers of distinguished personalities.', 'Lobster, Teppanyaki Goose Liver, Teppanyaki Wagyu Beef Roll', '', 'Inakaya sits high above Hong Kong on the 101st floor of the International Commerce Centre. The menu draws on 40 years of history in Tokyo, featuring superb robatayaki and teppanyaki. In addition to grilled morsels, sushi and kaiseki options grace the menu. The restaurant lobby boasts an autumn harvest scene, exuding warmth. Just past the wine library is a chic bar with a mirror that reflects a spectacular view of the city. The décor evokes a modern Zen interpretation of a traditional sake brewery— complete with sake barrels, dark wood furniture and wenge flooring—providing an authentic Japanese atmosphere. The main dining area features a raised platform and movable screens, further elevating the tranquil ambience.
**All the booking through EZTABLE will need to be confirmed by Inakaya**', '5 -min walk from MTR Kowloon station Exit B', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3255, 'en_US', 'Hooray Bar & Restaurant', 'Enjoy the stunning Victoria Harbour view with outdoor seating in Hooray Bar!', 'Caesar Salad with Smoked Salmon, White Eel with Eel Sauce', '', 'The restaurant serves a wide variety of dishes that range from American style grilled steaks, charcoal grilled skewers, Italian pizza and pasta. It is also a perfect spot for chill-out drinks. 
Hooray Bar & Restaurant boasts the biggest alfresco dining area in Hong Kong, with a spectacular terrace that overlooks Victoria Harbour. The elegant wood furniture on the 220 seat terrace is surrounded by luscious foliage, creating a relaxing respite from the bustling city below. Hooray is a great spot for a long lunch, a chic evening gathering, and is also an excellent venue for private parties and events.
**All the booking through EZTABLE will need to be confirmed by Hooray Bar & Restaurant **', '5 -min walk from MTR Causeway Bay station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3257, 'en_US', 'Mekiki No Ginji (World Trade Centre)', 'Great selection of Japanese fresh seafood, Izakaya\' spirit & vibe from Okinawa', 'BBQ Oyster with Urchin Sauce, Mentaiko Egg Omelette Roll', '', 'Mekiki no Ginji, revolutionizing izakaya traditions, sets itself apart from others with an encompassing menu that includes each Japanese prefecture’s signature dish. The dishes are innovative while paying tribute to regional cooking method with local ingredients. Each dish in the menu represents the prefecture’s unique food culture and the menu is splendid with more than 60 options including appetizers, salads, grills, rice, noodles, shabu-shabu, sushi & sashimi and desserts.
The setting in Ginji sets a modern and convivial tone with clean furnishings and a wooden ceiling that is carved with food item names written in Japanese. Inviting you to the restaurant is a line of big wooden barrel that boasts a sharp Japanese sense and a gigantic U-shape wooden table that showcases a colorful array of ingredients. The restaurant also makes use of live tempura, robatayaki, and sushi stations that invite you to the exciting dining scene. Parties or gathering within small groups are very welcome to be seated in the ‘Ginji Barrel’ especially designed for diners who look for more space and privacy.
