(3872, 'en_US', 'Little Break Coffee & Kitchen', 'Let\'s take a little break! Enjoy the specialty coffee here', 'French Blue Mussels, All Day Breakfast, Charco Grill Australia M5 Wagyu', '', 'Little Break Coffee & Kitchen aims to offer a place for you to escape from the busy daily life. You can enjoy their specialty coffee and fine food with the friendly service. The host of this cafe is two student graduated from HKU, this cafe is their dreamland. The dreamland named as Little Break. In the crowded city, let\'s you have a little break..', '2 -min walk from MTR Lai Chi Kok station Exit D3', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3874, 'en_US', 'HIGE Izakaya - ひげ 髭', 'Traditional Japanese Izakaya here like you are in Japan! Must try the Spanish red prawns!', 'Spanish Red Prawns, Crispy Dried Puffer Fish, HIGE Sausage', '', 'HIGE Izakaya - ひげ 髭 is located in the Mid-level of Central. You can experience the traditional Japanese Izakaya here like you are in Japan. HIGE offers different variety of seasonal dishes and wine e.g. Sake, Japanese Whisky and cocktail for your friends gathering. You must try the Spanish red prawns!', '20 -min walk from MTR Central station Exit D1', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(4413, 'en_US', 'Ciao Ristorante Italiano', 'The main north-south authentic Italian cuisine', 'Italian Beef Carpaccio, Smoke Duck Breast Salad with Mixed Vegetables', '', 'Ciao offers a generally nice atmosphere, good Italian food, and a broad variety of selections. The set price dinner menu is served every night and serve you the most seasonal dishes. You can enjoy different drinks here with only little extra. Salad and starters are served buffet style from one or two serving lines.', 'Bus: 53、234A、234B、234C、962B、52X、261B\nMini Bus: 96、96M、302、308M', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(4114, 'en_US', 'Kum Lo Hotpot', 'Unique duck stock for hotpot in Jordan', 'Duck Stock Base, Shrimp Fries, Lobster Sashimi', '', 'The owner has very greasy mouth, because of the working relationship,he often go to different places, so seeking food  was part of his life.Saying once, he went to work in Northeast China, he tasted a very sweet soup - Laoya, after returning to Hong Kong, he has missed Laoya taste, but Hong Kong has not the same type of food,So he opened the \"Kum Lo\", so that more people can enjoy the best of this class cuisine.
