(2763, 'en_US', 'YAKINIKU GREAT', 'YAKINKU GREAT, the first overseas branch from Japan Utsunomiya.', 'Misuji, Kyoto Style Yaki, shabu, Snowflake Beef', '', 'YAKINKU GREAT, the first overseas branch from Japan Utsunomiya. Different of other Yakiniku restaurant, YAKINKU GREAT specializes with provide black cattle, including the popularity NO. 1 rare parts ─Misuji! Let you to Feeling non-ordinary black beef Yakiniku! The interiors at Yakiniku Great are simple, with grill-centred wooden tables sitting next to whitewashed walls. Chef Tsugawa has clearly spent a lot of time analysing each cut and timing the grilling to perfection so you get the best out of the flavours. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit A1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2764, 'en_US', 'Hanabi', 'Chef  Michael , had design the non conventional Omasake, some new style creative dishes.', 'Omakase', '', 'Hanabi, Japanese restaurant. Quiet environment that need not worry about noisy bar music when eating Japanese food. Chef  Michael , had design the non conventional Omasake, some new style creative dishes. He use the Miso sauce with grapefruit, to instead soy sauce when you eatting the sashimi, a bit acid but taste good.  \nOmasake at dinner about $800 & $1,200 two choice. Two difference set basically including appetizers, sashimi, soups, sushi and desserts. Menu will change in every month, make guests keep of freshness (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2765, 'en_US', 'KYO JAPANESE', 'Daily fresh fish shipped from Japan to Hong Kong, is of the most seasonal seafood.', 'Omakase', '', 'KYO JAPANESE located near Davis Street, Kennedy Town, Western District, in the vicinity are restaurant of many western style occupied. Chef Wong Ka Lok worked as a sushi chef in Imamura, Miso and other Japanese restaurant. So our experience of the chef is no doubt, his variety of fish food rules and with great confidence and technique. Omakase is highly recommend said by chef Wong, each of which is a daily fresh fish shipped from Japan to Hong Kong, is of the most seasonal seafood. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C, Kennedy Town MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2766, 'en_US', 'Dine-Art Cosimo Private Chef', 'Morden desgin and using the highest quality of ingredients imported from Italy', 'Roasted Australian Lamb Rack, Sicilian Red Prawns, Home made Ricotta Cheese stuffed Ravioli', '', 'Located on Wong Chuk Hang in a modern 4,000 Sqf Art Space. Dine-Art Private Kitchen offers only 24 seats. The Walls are adorned with exquisite fine artworks from the wall-know Australian painter Fred Williams to the Famous Chinese artist Zao Wou Ki.\n Dine-art Private Kitchen is a uniquely exclusive and intimate private dining experience. Chef Cosimo Taddei inspires diners with an elegant mix of Florentine flair and imagination.\n Using the highest quality of ingredients imported from Italy, Chef Cosimo transports his diners on an unforgettable culinary journey. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', 'Take bus No.72,77,38,42 from Causeway Bay, stop at Nam Long Shan', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2767, 'en_US', 'IPPOH tempura restaurant', 'IPPOH, Implement the Low-key style, specialized in Tempura.', 'Tempura, Basil leaves Tempura', '', 'Implement the Low-key style, a Mupai of IPPOH hang outside, not many people know what IPPOH is and pass away. Chef ToyoSeki, specialized in making Tempura. When you get in, need to knock on the door, and follow the staff\'s direct, unauthorized person cannot get in. IPPOH attention to the guests privacy. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2768, 'en_US', 'Uehara', 'The boss of Uehara focus on every details of the restaurant, include the tableware, seafood  all are imported from Japan.', 'Omakase', '', 'The name of the restaurant Uehara is named by the first name of the boss. The boss focus on every details of the restaurant, include the tableware all are imported from Japan. Seafood are also imported from Japan in season. Also, the rice are mix with Hokkaidō rice and the Sushi rice, which have a better taste-texture. Moreover, the sushi vinegar are mixed with white vinegar and red vinegar, which is very suitable for using on the fish sashimi. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit E, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2769, 'en_US', 'Thirty Eight', 'The target and concept of Thirty-Eight is to have a perfect dining experience, exactly like you would have it in Japan.', 'Perigord truffle A5 wagyu beef, Sea Trout', '', 'The target and concept of Thirty-Eight is to have a perfect dining experience, exactly like you would have it in Japan. Our private lift acts like a time tunnel and takes you to a place where everything used comes straight from Japan and is of the highest possible quality. With only three private rooms and perfectly trained staff, adhering to the strictest rules to assure the privacy of our guests, Thirty-Eight provides you a way to escape from Hong Kong for a few hours. We are located on the first floor of the Gramercy Building on 38 Caine Road. The entrance to Thirty-Eight is through our own private elevator, located to the left of the IPC Foodlab. Please use the intercom to the left of the elevator to notify us of your arrival. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2770, 'en_US', 'Holytan Grill', 'HOLYTAN slows cook the fine ingredients both from Japan and France, we also serve live seafood dishes with Japanese and French touch.', 'Grilled Kagoshima Wagyu Beef Tenderloin, Shrimp Bisque', '', 'Located at the historical Pottinger Street, HOLYTAN has opened to serve a special Wagyu grill which using an unique and made by Japan Far Infrared Oven to slow cook the fine ingredients both from Japan and France, we also serve live seafood dishes with Japanese and French touch. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2771, 'en_US', 'Sushi Mori Tomoaki', 'Design concept of orthodox sushi restaurant. Customer can see the chef making sushi clearly.', 'Omakase', '', 'The restaurant is not big, no VIP seat and only can accommodate twelve customer. Design concept of orthodox sushi restaurant. Customer can see the chef making sushi clearly. You can have the Omakase no matter lunch or dinner. Also it have provide some Seasonal dishes. You can ask Mr. Sen what you want. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit A, Fortress Hill MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2772, 'en_US', 'Forum Restaurant', 'Forum Restaurant is a Cantonese restaurant established in 1977, Run by Hong Kong\'s international chef and ambassador of Chinese cuisine, Yeung Koon Yat.', 'Braised Goose Liver in Abalone Sauce, Braised Shark’s Fin with Abalone in Brown Sauce, Braised Crab Shell Shark’s Fin', '', 'Forum Restaurant  is a Cantonese restaurant established in 1977, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong. Run by Hong Kong\'s international chef and ambassador of Chinese cuisine, Yeung Koon Yat , it is one of the best known eateries in Hong Kong.\nThe restaurant is frequented by the glitterati of Hong Kong (many of whom are regulars) and is not traditionally an expatriate or tourist attraction.\nYeung Koon Yat\'s signature dish Ah Yat\'s Abalone is famous all around the world. The abalone offered can cost an average of US$7200 per kilogram. Apart from the more expensive and rarer Cantonese specialities, local dishes are also offered at a more modest price. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit C, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2773, 'en_US', 'Aberdeen Street Social (upstairs)', 'Aberdeen Street Social is a restaurant and bar at PMQ. Serving up modern British fare as well as cocktails', 'Raw Hokkaido scallops, dashi jelly, apple, shiso, avocado and wasabi purée, Pork chop, pumpkin and orange puree, pine nut dressing, JAAL 75% chocolate, banana, calamansi, Madras curry', '', 'Restaurant, Cocktail Bar & Café. Michelin star Chef Jason Atherton’s latest “social” venue at PMQ. Aberdeen Street Social is the third collaboration in Hong Kong between Michelin-star Chef Jason Atherton and entrepreneur Yenn Wong. Following on his recent highly successful openings in London, Aberdeen Street Social serves Atherton’s modern British cuisine, bar bites, desserts and drinks to play. Designed by the award-winning Neri & Hu, the bright and airy 2-floored venue has outdoor terraces on both floors and a garden terrace surrounding the property. Upstairs houses a contemporary restaurant inviting an intimate dining experience, with a private room and balcony overlooking the gardens. Downstairs is a Cocktail Bar & Café, a buzzy all-day space for casual dining inside or on the outdoor patio which spills out to landscaped gardens. Also on the premises is Sweet Social, a unique retail shop on the garden level, selling home-made pastries, gelati, chocolates and beverages, to enjoy at the venue or take away. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2774, 'en_US', 'Catalunya Hong Kong', 'The restaurant boasts a fantastic selection of Spanish wines, Mediterranean hospitality, professional yet friendly service, and cutting-edge cocktails.', 'Ham, cheese and truffle bikini, Seafood paella, “Torrija” with smoked milk ice cream', '', 'Catalunya Hong Kong features contemporary Spanish cuisine which draws inspiration from authentic Catalan recipes. The restaurant boasts a fantastic selection of Spanish wines, Mediterranean hospitality, professional yet friendly service, and cutting-edge cocktails. Our kitchen is helmed by an international team of award-winning culinary experts from some of the world’s best Spanish restaurants such as elBulli, El Celler de Can Roca, Mugaritz, Arzak, and Restaurante Martín Berasategui. Designed by award-winning design firm, Avroko of New York, it is the sister restaurant of Catalunya Singapore, which has received rave reviews since opening in August 2012. The restaurant will seat 140, including a private room for 16 persons. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2775, 'en_US', 'Mott 32', '“The most important component to a dish is fresh ingredients,” Mott 32 .', 'Apple wood roasted Peking duck, Barbecue prime Iberico pork with Yellow Mountain honey, Kurobuta pork, soft quail egg, black trufﬂe siu mai', '', 'Mott 32 is named after 32 Mott Street in New York.\nMott 32 believe strongly in the core principles of farm-to-table cooking. The provenance of the ingredients is very important to us. Mott 32 is an attempt to shift the focus back onto ingredients and recipes passed down from generation-to-generation. \nMott 32\'s cooking is principally Cantonese with some signature Sichuan and Beijing dishes. Our custom industrial duck oven and special air-drying duck fridge is a central feature of the restaurant. We roast ducks both in the Cantonese and Beijing method with our Peking Duck only available for dinner and by pre order only.\nChef Fung strongly believes in using great ingredients, and letting the true flavours of the ingredients shine in his dishes. “The most important component to a dish is fresh ingredients,” says Chef Fung. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit K, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2776, 'en_US', 'Mano', 'Mano is a place for Hong Kong’s culinary cognoscenti. It redefines all-day dining for those who live for a surprise.', 'Roast Duck, Beetroot tartare with quail egg yolk and mustard seeds', '', 'Mano is a place for Hong Kong’s culinary cognoscenti. It redefines all-day dining for those who live for a surprise. For the open-minded and vivacious. It’s for the bold and the understated. Coffee, culture, collaboration, cocktails, curiousity; we\'re born from a world of whimsy where wine meets the limitless wilderness of fresh ingredients and the beauty of biology blooms amidst an urban jungle. Mano is for those with a song stirring in their heads and a skip in their step. We’re good taste and exceptional quality, slathered, sliced and served. Mano is Hong Kong’s hideaway. Tucked into the ground floor of L Place, Central, we’re set back from the bustle – but still have a great view of it. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2777, 'en_US', 'Seasons by Olivier Elzer', 'Hong Kong’s newest venue for creative French cuisine.', 'French pink radish, Guérande salt and homemade butter, Grilled langoustine, risotto venere and masala butter, Grilled Holstein rib, eye, shallots cooked in red wine sauce', '', 'Hong Kong’s newest venue for creative French cuisine. The creation of executive chef Olivier Elzer, Seasons is a nuanced reinvention of French cuisine in the heart of modern Asia. A cosmopolitan and smart-casual French restaurant, Seasons places an emphasis on intimacy over austerity, comfort over conformity and quality over all else. Avoiding the wrappings of pretention, the relaxed ambience of Seasons by Olivier Elzer unfolds around its open kitchen, creating a vibrant, welcoming atmosphere where executive chef Olivier Elzer performs an arm’s length and a heartbeat away. Like the passage of time itself, Seasons is in calm but constant transition, refining and redefining itself in a fluid, harmonious evolution. Chef Olivier’s philosophy is one of inclusion, pairing a classical understanding of French cuisine with a modern Asian sensibility and unbridled delight in the finest ingredients, not just from France, but from the world at large. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2778, 'en_US', 'Serge et Le Phoque', 'Serge et Le Phoque provide best highest quality ingredients from all across the world.', 'Boeuf a cru, sea urchin, chrysanthemum flowers, Scallops with garlic roots, Dacquoise', '', 'Forget about your expectations when arriving for dinner at Serge; we are offering our take on French fine dining. - La Food: best highest quality ingredients from all across the world. “A la minute” cooking (nothing is pre-cooked or prepared in advance). Minimal cuisine in which traditional French layers are removed. - Les Wines: mostly French and naturals – see our wine menu. - Le Service: causal but attentive. - Le Space: raw and yes our toilets are in the carpark but they are ours and they are clean. - Les menus; a shorter menu, Le Petit Serge at $650 and a larger one, Le Grand Phoque at $850. Both of our menus are at the chef’s discretion; meaning that we choose for you and make sure you’ll enjoy the ride. We, of course, adjust to any food restrictions or to whatever ingredients you do not feel like eating tonight. Add on for the cote de boeuf, from Parisian butcher, Hugo desnoyer. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit A3, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2779, 'en_US', 'Quest', 'Built upon sturdy foundations based on the skill and creativity of Chef Dang, Quest aims to celebrate inspiration with inventive and playful tasting menus.', 'The Boston lobster tail rice paper roll with pickled daikon, avocado and a smoked paprika sauce, Beef pho tartare, Braised oxtail bun bo hue with daikon and tripe', '', 'Located in the heart of Wan Chai, Quest is the newest venture from renowned chef Que Vinh Dang. Built upon sturdy foundations based on the skill and creativity of Chef Dang, Quest aims to celebrate inspiration with inventive and playful tasting menus. From its perch overlooking the city, Quest offers guests an elevated yet relaxed dining experience. Quest\'s contemporary decor speaks of edgy sophistication with a sleek, monochromatic look. The restaurant itself benefits from its address on the 28th floor of a glittering new building in Wan Chai, boasting city views that add to the appeal of the space. Quest\'s menu promises to take diners on a journey of taste. Chef Dang has specified that menus will only be distributed upon the meal\'s completion, allowing him to surprise guests course after course in ingredient-driven degustation menus. Modeled after his personal interests and inspirations, the meals will explore flavours with classic-meets-modern cooking techniques, showcasing the chef\'s inherent talent for creation. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit A4, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2780, 'en_US', 'ON Dining kitchen & Lounge', 'ON Dining Kitchen & Lounge , focusing on southern European and Mediterranean flavors.', 'The roasted pigeon with artichokes and lemon chutney, Quail and lobster pie, Iconic 63C eggs', '', 'ON Dining Kitchen & Lounge is the new restaurant from Chef Philippe Orrico of the newly minted 1 star Upper Modern Bistro, focusing on southern European and Mediterranean flavors. Located on the 28th & 29th floor, the lounge boasts views of Central through its outdoor terrace while the formal dining space is located downstairs. Set lunch is priced at HK$288 for 2 courses or HK$328 for 3 courses. on the 29 Floor, you will enter on to a plush lounge area with velvet blue chairs and a small terrace for outdoor dining. Downstairs is the main dining room where an open kitchen bounded by white marble walls emits a classy 50s feel, alongside accents of red curtaining opposite. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2781, 'en_US', 'Arcane', 'Arcane serves modern European cuisine presented in an A la carte menu, alongside daily specials and set lunch menu.', 'Wagyu beef short rib, Pan, fried Sawara mackerel with creamy Jerusalem artichoke purée, pickled trompette mushrooms and lemon oil', '', 'Multi-award winning chef, Shane Osborn, the first Australian Chef to achieve one and two Michelin stars at Pied-a-Terre in London, has opened his new solo venture, Arcane in Central, Hong Kong. Arcane serves modern European cuisine presented in an A la carte menu, alongside daily specials and set lunch menu. Menus will be seasonally lead, utilising the finest produce from Japan, France and the UK. The 2000 square foot space houses artworks by Flowers Gallery, a London and New York based contemporary art gallery. Oak is used throughout the restaurant on the floors, while tabletops are covered with crisp linen, silverware and stemware supplied by Bernadaud, Zalto and David Mellor. The terrace is designed as an English tropical garden; lush greenery acts as hedges surrounding the dining area with fresh kitchen garden growing a selection of 30 different varieties of herbs, fruits and vegetables that will feature on the menu. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2782, 'en_US', 'Gradini Ristorante e Bar Italiano', 'Gradini Ristorante E Bar Italiano in The Pottinger Hong Kong specialises in classic Italian dishes.', 'Salt crusted whole line, caught sea bassass, Classic tiramisu', '', 'Gradini Ristorante E Bar Italiano in The Pottinger Hong Kong specialises in classic Italian dishes. Hearty Italian flavours are amplified by the elegant ambience of the restaurant and the historically-rich neighbourhood in Central. Drawing inspiration from the freshest ingredients and time-honoured recipes, signature dishes include “Grilled Mediterranean Octopus with Citrus Salad on Hand-Picked Baby Spinach Leave”, “Pasta with Tuscan Sausage in Spicy Tomato Sauce with Parmesan Cheese”, “Salt-Crusted whole Italian Line-Caught Sea Bass with Herbs” and many more. Adjacent to the dining room is an intimate bar, which provides a sophisticated hideaway from the city’s bustle. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit D, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2783, 'en_US', 'Town', 'Set in Causeway Bay\'s prestigious Cubus Building, Town brings innovative food and chic design together to create a unique and enjoyable dining experience.', 'Sicilian red prawn carpaccio with yuzu, croutons and black truffle caviar, Suckling pig, clams, pancetta, baby spinach and miso broth', '', 'Set in Causeway Bay\'s prestigious Cubus Building, Town brings innovative food and chic design together to create a unique and enjoyable dining experience. Chef Bryan Nagao, recipes are a fusion of classic and modern, and show not only his experience from his Hawaiian roots but techniques he picked up from his impressive resume. Favourite dishes included the beautifully presented and fresh Sicilian Red Prawn Carpaccio with black truffle caviar, yuzu and croutons, the healthy and flavourful Hawaiian Hearts Of Palm with red quinoa, endive, figs, pumpkin and black garlic and the insanely delicious House Made Black Ink Udon with Spanish prawn, scallop, shiso and gremolata. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2784, 'en_US', 'The Continental', 'The Continental is an elegant all-day restaurant. Each dish is created in response to pure ingredients presented beautifully.', 'Parmesan soufflé suissesse with tomato and anchovy sauce, Rib Eye Steak', '', 'Inspired by the sophisticated charm of Europe\'s grand cafés, The Continental is an elegant all-day restaurant. Spacious yet intimate, the contemporary design by David Collins Studio complements Rowley Leigh\'s celebrated cuisine. The Continental presents a menu of lovingly refined dishes. Rowley Leigh is one of the leading lights of modern British cooking. A respected chef, restaurateur and award-winning writer, Leigh apprenticed with the Roux brothers at Le Gavroche before moving to Kensington Place in 1987 as Head Chef. He opened the acclaimed Le Café Anglais in 2007 and writes a weekly column about food for the Financial Times. In the words of Rowley Leigh himself, \"the menu is Anglo French with a British sensibility\". Each dish is created in response to pure ingredients presented beautifully. Service is from breakfast through lunch and dinner, to late night drinks and snacks. The perfect all-day space to unwind in the city. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit F, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2785, 'en_US', 'Gaucho', 'Famous for its sumptuous steaks and mouth-watering ceviches, adds a touch of Argentine culinary and cultural passion to Hong Kong’s dining scene.', '48, hour dry aged Provoleta, Tira de Ancho Ribeye', '', 'London\'s award-winning Argentine restaurant opens its first outpost in Asia in Hong Kong. Located in the heart of the busy commercial centre on Queen’s Road Central, Gaucho, famous for its sumptuous steaks and mouth-watering ceviches, adds a touch of Argentine culinary and cultural passion to Hong Kong’s dining scene. The venue can be configured in a variety of layouts to suit your requirements, whether it is exclusive hire of the whole of Gaucho, just the lounge, the wine room or a private dining room. With the help of our events manager and the team, we will work with you to create a bespoke events package. Gaucho offers award-winning Argentine Ceviches, traditional Empanadas and renowned steak cuts from the finest free-range Argentine Angus beef, together with a world famous wine cellar boasting premium Argentine Wines. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2786, 'en_US', 'Toritama', 'Yakitori have a menu of over 20 different chicken parts, serving the adventurous, gluttonous, foodie and skewer experts.', 'Misaki (Tail of hen), Mitarashi Ice (soy sauce ice, cream)', '', 'Located towards the top of Glenealy Street in the popular district of Central, Toritama is a short walk up from Pedder Street through Lan Kwai Fong. Then head up a little bit to the left of LKF and you will find us on a peaceful side street but still a stones throw away from the trendy bar and dining scene of Central & Soho. Tokyo’s most authentic neighborhood Yakitori joint Toritama, has finally arrived in Hong Kong. Bringing over techniques from master griller Shiro Izawa, we have a menu of over 20 different chicken parts, serving the adventurous, gluttonous, foodie and skewer experts. We are so happy to be included as a rising star in CNN\'s list of \'Hot in Hong Kong: 12 best restaurants for 2015\'! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2787, 'en_US', 'Neighborhood', 'Neighbourhood serves perfect dishes, providing family-style pan-European cuisine.', 'Chocolate palette', '', 'Chef and restaurateur David Lai is a legendary homegrown, stick with local ingredients. For a long time, his first restaurant loved by regular customers. In Neighbourhood, he created the perfect dishes, providing family-style pan-European cuisine. Nothing too fancy here, but each dish is carefully prepared on a rotating menu. David Lai creates the nicely neighborhood French-inflected restaurant in a tiny block located behind one of Central\'s busiest area, David Lai\'s Neighborhood provides you the refreshing site of Hollywood Road, mentally slowing you down to enjoy a well-made meal. Bring a friend, or three, sharing like fried frog legs and simple pasta and grilled meat snacks daily. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2788, 'en_US', 'Risi e Bisi', 'We serve liquor and Italian bar food to enjoy against the backdrop of New York style electro-pop and our fun drinks offering.', 'Fried Scarmoza, Strozzapreti pasta with chilli ‘nduja and homemade sausage, 72 Hour Spare Rib', '', 'RISI e BISI is a funky, relaxed lounge bar serving craft beers, specialised cocktails, Japanese whiskies and Mediterranean wines by the carafe. We serve Italian bar food to enjoy against the backdrop of New York style electro-pop and our fun drinks offering. Dimly lit and cosy with low hanging lights, exposed brickwork and edgy photography create and intimate, yet raw atmosphere. RISI e BISI is a bacaro – local neighbourhood winebar - serving cocktails based on artisan spirit, craft beers and fun Italian wines. The food is a selection of bar food featuring homemade pastas, meatballs and a range of meat and seafood dishes done on a chargrill. Open from 5pm til late, with upbeat lounge music and a buzzy vibe, RISI e BISI is a great place to chill it with friends. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2789, 'en_US', 'Sohofama', 'SOHOFAMA is where urban farming meets comfort Chinese cuisine for the Hong Kong of today.', 'Black Truffle Xiao Long Bao, 24 Hour Drunken Prawns, Tea Smoked Duck', '', 'SOHOFAMA is where urban farming meets comfort Chinese cuisine for the Hong Kong of today. SOHOFAMA’s goal in any of its projects is to raise awareness for healthier living through serving good, chemical-free food, including locally grown ingredients which support the community, and organic ingredients, which support the body. Drawing on the Chinese tradition, we have created seasonal herbal soup selections, designed to suit a range of wellness needs of the urban dweller. Our menu is carefully balance to reflect both the old and the new with some dishes reflecting childhood favorites, while others celebrate the multiculturalism of today\'s HK society in dishes, and absolutely no MSG or chicken powder. Instead, we use freshly grown herbs for taste and slow cooked chicken broth to fully enhance flavours. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2790, 'en_US', 'Lazy Hog', 'Lazy Hog uses the most seasonal ingredients, cooked with the most innovative ways.', 'Watermelon tartare, Pig ear nachos', '', 'From farms to table, Lazy Hog uses the most seasonal ingredients, cooked with the most innovative ways. The restaurant focuses on fusion cuisine that merges traditional American cooking with modern methods .It has some of the most innovative and talented chefs every day and continue to create culinary masterpieces and remodeling, it has become a well-known Hong Kong restaurant. Delicate dishes served by chef with passion by former chef of Catalunya, certainly in the vicinity of the restaurant played tricks. New American food means taking food at a higher stage. Lazy Hog serves \"New American\" cuisine, Lazy Hog is a practical and authentic restaurant that can immediately make the diners feel relaxed and comfortable. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2791, 'en_US', 'Isono Eatery & Bar', 'Isono is a relaxed eatery and bar, serving bold, Mediterranean dishes made for sharing with friends.', 'Selection of Roasted Iberian Pork Shoulder, Chorizo & Morcilla, Beef Tartare w/ Organic Egg & Truffle Mayonnaise, Piemonte hazelnut crème brulee', '', 'Isono is a relaxed eatery and bar, serving bold, Mediterranean dishes made for sharing with friends. Isono is not long after the start, located in a newly renovated building called PMQ (Police Married Quarters), the rapid growth of a foodie destination, there are design galleries and emerging inside restaurants and bars. Isono restaurant concepts’ are from Basque cuisine, the Mediterranean (France, Spain and Italy), offers an interesting and delicious cuisine, the idea is quite interesting. The culinary team is led by Chef Paolo Casagrande. Together with his team, they hope to bring their childhood flavors and feelings of nostalgia to the foodies in Hong Kong. The menu will feature homemade Italian pastas, hearty French stews and Spanish roast meats, and a wide range of seafood, cheeses, olive oils and cured meats. Environment is very beautiful, comfortable and with modern settings which create a casual feeling, warm atmosphere, plus some smiling services from waiters. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2792, 'en_US', 'Jamie\'s Italian', 'Jamie\'s Italian is inspired by Jamie’s passion for the Italian way of life.', 'Lamb Lollipops, Salted caramel gelato', '', 'Jamie\'s Italian was founded in Oxford in 2008. Since then it has grown to more than 30 restaurants worldwide, and there are already plans for even more in towns, counties and countries around the world. Our menu is rooted in authenticity. We’re all about fantastic, rustic dishes created using tried and tested recipes. Jamie’s friend and mentor, Gennaro Contaldo, has added substance to what is now the essence of Jamie’s Italian – tradition combined with current, innovative ideas and a Jamie twist. We work hard to find the very best ingredients, which are meticulously sourced from producers, both in Italy and around the UK, who share our ethos and take enormous pride in what they do. In turn, this inspires the team at Jamie’s Italian and we train our staff to have a thorough knowledge of all the dishes that we serve. We teach the origin of each dish, how the dishes have been created and cooked, and the personalities and stories behind them all. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit B, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2793, 'en_US', 'NOM- Not Only Meatballs', 'If you like meatballs, sliders, pizza, a dining experience just like at home and a few cheeky negronis, NOM is the place for you.', 'meat ball, hamburger, pizza', '', 'NOM is the distillation of more than a decade of experience, sacrifice, sweat, hard work, passion, tears, drunken nights, love, research, trips, reading and advice from mentors. When we were thinking about a new food and beverage concept for Hong Kong, we didn’t want to create just ‘another Italian restaurant’. We realised that what people want is comfort food in a friendly place. We arrived to our idea of NOM: a meatball bar that’s cheap and cheerful, combined with a restaurant that’s modern and sophisticated. NOM will help people in Hong Kong understand that something simple as meatballs can also be refined and really enjoyable. Our customers will be able to taste great Italian food without spending a fortune. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2794, 'en_US', 'Ho Lee Fook', 'Chef Jowett Yu\'s inventive approach to Chinese flavours is best enjoyed with an open mind and a strong appetite.', 'Mom’s “mostly cabbage a little bit of pork” dumplings with sacha soy dressing, Taiwanese style lu rou rice, Yunnan style wagyu steak tartare with hot and sour sauce', '', 'Ho Lee Fook “good fortune for your mouth” is a funky Chinese kitchen inspired by old school Hong Kong cha chaan tengs and the spirit of late-night Chinatown hangouts in 1960’s New York. The most noticeable thing is when you walk into the restaurant, you can look straight into the clean, open-style kitchen, and you also see the giant waving lucky cat, the experience is so great. Taiwanese-born chef Jowett Yu’s inventive approach to Chinese flavours is best enjoyed with an open mind and a strong appetite. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2795, 'en_US', 'Check-In Taipei', 'Redefining the Taiwanese culinary experience through delicately crafted food and drinks to arouse your five senses.', 'Chicken and Waffle, Taro Cheesecake', '', 'Check-in Taipei in Soho brings contemporary Taiwanese cuisine to a brand new level of sophistication to Hong Kong. With a mission to tantalise your taste buds, this new and upcoming destination seeks to redefine the Taiwanese culinary experience through its delicately crafted food and drinks, redefining the Taiwanese culinary experience through delicately crafted food and drinks to arouse your five senses. Innovative morsels that defy tradition, veggie dishes that celebrate the taste of nature, back to basics that keep you satisfied, and luscious desserts to wrap up the meal on a sweet note. Embark on the tasty adventure with friends at Check-in Taipei. Liven up your meal with imaginative signature drinks and cocktails crafted by our Drinks Architect from Taiwan. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit C, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2796, 'en_US', 'Sushi To by Harlan Goldstein', 'Sushi To by Harlan Goldstein plays host to guests looking for the perfect dining experience in a bold and sensual setting.', 'Harlan G’s Funky Maki Rolls', '', 'Acclaimed Chef Harlan Goldstein breaks new ground with Gold. With its contemporary European menu, inviting bat scene and sophisticated atmosphere, it plays host to guests looking for the perfect dining experience in a bold and sensual setting. Harlan Goldstein has eaten in many Japanese Restaurants all over the world. He must say Chef Maeda san new menu dishes are packed with flavor, amazing creativity, in the hottest place in town! Using only the highest quality ingredients and fresh, seasonal produce from artisans farms it aims to set new standards in creativity. Gold features a menu filled with imaginative interpretations of classic and modern cuisine. Come join us at Midtown for the ultimate experience - fantastic food, amazing service. Chef Maeda-San will bring an exquisite Fireworks Course Menu at Sushi To, overlooking the unsurpassed panoramic view of Victoria Harbour. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit B, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2797, 'en_US', 'Naked Gurume Gyarari', 'The cuisine at NAKED Gurume Gyarari is highly contemporary and ingredients-driven, conforming with the global movement towards healthier, more considered food choices.', 'Toro y 48 Months Iberico Ham Wrap, Lobster Risotto Bisque, Strawberry Gasm', '', 'Founded by visionary, Patrick Wai, who comes from years of experience in the international design field, and Executive Chef Justin Chan, a Hong Kong-born chef, with global experience rooted in his regional Asian Heritage, which includes Chinese, Laotian and Portuguese ancestry. He borrows cooking methods from his childhood and from his travels around the world, with pioneering results. The cuisine at NAKED Gurume Gyarari is highly contemporary and ingredients-driven, conforming with the global movement towards healthier, more considered food choices. As Gurume Gyarari stands for Gourmet Gallery, our concept is to deliver an intensified moment of unique dining experience through complex interactions of Art, Design, Leisure and Gourmet. Designs of dishes were carefully thought-out by Patrick Wai, using his architectural point of view to further re-define the concept of NAKED. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2798, 'en_US', 'Cocotte', 'Cocotte looks forward to welcoming you to our petit slice of Paris in the heart of Hong Kong’s dining district.', 'French whole dover sole \"Meuniere\", Steak Tartare \"Cocotte Style\"', '', 'A Parisian brasserie-inspired restaurant in the quaint neighbourhood of NoHo. Cocotte is the chic, relaxed and casual concept of French brothers Jonathan and Brice Moldovan. Designed as an intimate, vibrant space featuring eclectic wallpapers, mid-century lines and art deco curves. Cocotte focuses on seasonal ingredients with a menu revolving around the “less is more” philosophy, presenting a refined and modern take on French favourites. We look forward to welcoming you to our petit slice of Paris in the heart of Hong Kong’s dining district. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2799, 'en_US', 'Sanche Modern Korean', 'SANCHE delivers the true flavor of Korean foods yet presenting the food in a modern tapas style.', 'kimchi pancake, great kalbi', '', 'SANCHE means naturally grown vegetables from the mountains of Korea and represents a core concept of Korean Cuisine, “healthy yet delicious”. SANCHE uses fresh ingredients from local suppliers and sources Jang, a traditional Korean sauce, directly from an artisan producer in Korea to deliver the true flavor of Korean foods yet presenting the food in a modern tapas style. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2800, 'en_US', 'Beef & Liberty', 'Beef & Liberty is our modern homage to the original beefsteak clubs and, we hope, the tastiest hamburger you will have tried in a while.', 'Lamb Burger, Classic Burger', '', 'Beef & Liberty is our modern homage to the original beefsteak clubs and, we hope, the tastiest hamburger you will have tried in a while. We proudly serve hormone-free grass-fed beef. Our beef is from Hereford and Angus cattle which are naturally raised by small-scale farmers in Cape Grim region of Tasmania, which has the cleanest air in the world. We freshly grind the beef in our burgers in-house, twice a day before lunch and dinner and serve it on a custom-baked white sour-dough roll. Add friends and family, top it off with some great craft beers, house cocktails or a fresh Liberty lemonade and you’ve got our version of what a perfect hamburger experience should be.” (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit F, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2801, 'en_US', 'Zafran', 'Zafran serves a mixture of traditional Spanish tapas-sized and larger dishes. Suitable for every kind of party dining.', 'Charcoal, grilled white and green asparagus, black truffle, Galician rock octopus, Boquerones and anchovies', '', 'Zafran is not only a tapas bar, Spanish restaurant, or late-night drinking and DJ lounge, but all three and more. Zafran serves a mixture of traditional Spanish tapas-sized and larger dishes and contemporary developments of these recipes. Designed to share, our dishes make up a menu that is versatile and suitable for a quick pit stop, romantic meal for two, extravagant family celebration or late night party dining.\n We also offer an expansive wine and spirit list, including Hong Kong\'s largest selection of Cava and a concise but expertly mixed selection of cocktails. Our three rooms are designed to be a world away from the traditional Spanish \'theme - restaurant\' with an industrial chic look that includes vintage aspects and some great examples of contemporary design classics - check out our amazing Tom Dixon light installations! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2802, 'en_US', 'Akrame', 'Restaurant Akrame has a future look of new generation of chefs who continue to pay tribute to classical French techniques.', 'Pineapple and charcoal, Lobster with lemon butter and pomegranate, Mussels with orange blossom and coconut', '', 'As Wan Chai’s Ship Street and surrounding streets continue to grow as a hot spot for those who are desperately seeking for good foods. At the end of last year, two Michelin-starred chef Akrame Benallal opened the second store of his famous Restaurant Akrame, the first of which is located in Paris. The chef says \"I begin a dish based on an idea, an ingredient, a feeling or sometimes a mood. I explore its gastronomic depths; it matures just like we do, over the course of service. Once the dish is finalised and I feel I cannot push the exploration or the composition any further, I stop serving it. Once successfully completed, I take it off the menu.\" The French chef replaces his menu items monthly and does not like to his dishes to stay the same at all time. Restaurant Akrame has a future look of new generation of chefs who continue to pay tribute to classical French techniques. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B2, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2803, 'en_US', 'Tabibito', 'Tabibito best represents our distinctive brand of Japanese Tapas with culinary inspirations from around the world.', 'Sweet corn tempura, Spicy wagyu tartar', '', 'Tabibito is our delicious new Okazu (Japanese Tapas) dining concept. The name Tabibito (旅人), means The Traveler in Japanese. It is inspired by our desire to creatively combine our favorite Japanese dishes with culinary methods we\'ve discovered whilst traveling around the world. Be sure to follow us on facebook for more delicious updates. Tabibito best represents our distinctive brand of Japanese Tapas with culinary inspirations from around the world. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2804, 'en_US', 'Man Mo Café', 'Man Mo Café creates authentic dishes that transform Cantonese culinary icon into something really quite masterpiece. You will be surprised to taste dim sum with a European touch.', 'Truffle Brie Dumplings, Foie Gras Xiao Long Bao', '', 'A contemporary and stylish restaurant featuring Cantonese and Western cuisine in the heart of Sheung Wan. Man Mo is the patent of Swiss dish expert Nicolas Elelouf. Elalouf could have gone for dim sum fusion just like some sort of arbitrary niche. But instead he has worked hard to create authentic dishes that transform this Cantonese culinary icon into something really quite masterpiece. His dream of fusion of East and West dim sum comes together through the expertise of his two fellow cooks, who had worked at Robuchon and Din Tai Fung before. Man Mo Cafe is perfect. It is located on one of last antique shop street of HK, a small place hidden way in the antiques section of Shueng Wan, you will be surprised to taste dim sum with a European touch. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2805, 'en_US', 'Le Port Parfumé', 'A refreshing simple menu is redrawn daily on a chalkboard representing our inspired take on the day\'s best produce.', 'Green asparagus and escargot in herb butter, Smoked pigeon with figs', '', 'At Le Port Parfumé we are dedicated to serving the freshest wild-caught seafood sourced directly from local fishermen who harvest the bounty of the sea from the cool depths of the waters around Hong Kong. A refreshing simple menu is redrawn daily on a chalkboard representing our inspired take on the day\'s best produce.\n At Le Port Parfumé we embrace cooking with spontaneity and creativity. We aim to break away from rigid, formulaic cuisine that leaves no room for surprise and ingenuity. We are constantly exploring new techniques and recipes to bring out the full exquisite flavours of the fresh ingredients they select. Our mantra is that seafood should be wild-caught not farmed. It is chilled but never frozen to fully preserve the delicate and subtle tastes and textures of each and every fish we serve. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2806, 'en_US', 'Harlan Goldstein\'s Comfort', 'Harlan Goldstein serves diverse modern European menu.', 'Caviar and salmon tartare, Spanish Duroc pork ribs, Apple crumble caramel with vanilla ice cream', '', 'The only place you will find the real Harlan now is at Gold by Harlan Goldstein.His flagship restaurant Gold by Harlan Gold stein has had remarkable achievements with the restaurant fully booked every night with reservations absolutely essential and the popular Saturday Brunch usually booked three weeks in advance. Gold by Harlan Goldstein’s diverse modern European menu is inspired by the ethnic and international cuisines of his Lower East Side New York roots. As always, diners can expect unique food from Goldstein whereby he puts his own twist with a variety of different techniques including smoking and slow cooking to maintain the natural flavor and moisture of ingredients. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2807, 'en_US', 'Upper Modern Bistro', 'Upper Modern Bistro is serving familiar French bistro dishes, French tapas and more elaborate haute cuisine.', 'The steak tartar served with parmesan cheese foam, avocado and pecan nuts, Frog leg and foie gras with cep bouillon', '', 'Upper Modern Bistro is serving familiar French bistro dishes, French tapas and more elaborate haute cuisine with an Asian twist using the best ingredients from all over the world. Our Upper Set Brunch offers up a selection of starters to share, a main, a choice of pastries to end with a glass of Champagne. Upper Modern Bistro is the vision of Philippe Orrico and his first solo venture since moving to Hong Kong seven years ago. Philippe arrived in Hong Kong in 2006 to set up Pierre at Mandarin Oriental, where he obtained one Michelin star, following this he joined Hullet House as Executive Chef at St. George. In 2012 he secured a Michelin star at St. George. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2808, 'en_US', 'Seventh Son Restaurant', 'Forging a new brand and vision of fine traditional Cantonese cooking destined to win the taste buds of customers across the globe.', 'Roast suckling pig, Stuffed baked crab shell, Rice in lotus leaf', '', 'True Cantonese cuisine is the heart of flavour. Here at Seventh Son Restaurant, we continue this celebration of a region rich in the treasures of the land, water and sky, through succulent signature dishes. We strive to the set the gold standard for Cantonese cuisine, by creating authentic classical feasts with the very finest ingredients. Our traditional cooking techniques strive to enhance the natural flavours and freshness of food, avoiding overpowering sauces and artificial additives. It is our hope to share the joy of true Cantonese culinary pleasure - from our hearts to your table. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit C, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2809, 'en_US', 'La Vache', 'La Vache! is a neighborhood steakhouse that provides a distinctively Parisian dining experience in the heart of Hong Kong’s vibrant Soho district.', 'Trimmed entrecôte rib, eye steak with frites, Croquembouche', '', 'La Vache! is a neighborhood steakhouse that provides a distinctively Parisian dining experience in the heart of Hong Kong’s vibrant Soho district. Inspired by the spirit of old Parisian brasseries, the restaurant pays homage to the renowned Relais de Venise by offering a simple menu where diners enjoy JUST ONE DISH: a green salad followed by steak frites served with generous pots of béarnaise sauce made according to La Vache! ‘s secret recipe. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2810, 'en_US', 'Fish & Meat', 'At Fish & Meat, we specialize in ingredients that speak for themselves and food that you crave week in, week out.', 'Slow, cooked Spanish Teruel pork belly porchetta ciabatta, Whole roasted Italian sea bass, Soft duck egg raviolo with ricotta cream', '', 'At Fish & Meat, we specialize in ingredients that speak for themselves and food that you crave week in, week out. Pairing back ingredients, each component of our dishes has been carefully sourced and cooked in an honest and rustic way. Salt that is packed full of minerals, olive oil with that peppery hit in the back of the throat, the finest whole sea bass that we could find, a handmade porchetta stuffed with Italian fennel sausage. All our pasta is homemade. Our cooking is honest and rustic whilst technique driven. Fundamentally, we want to provide carefully sourced farm-to-table ingredients that speak for themselves. Our dishes are designed to be shared, family style and have been cooked by a talented team, who simply focuses on the best produce and cooking methods, to perfect the fish, meat and homemade pasta dishes. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2811, 'en_US', 'Plat du Jour', 'Plat du Jour is a casual French trend with a bistro and is a little piece of Paris on Hoi Wan Street.', 'Steak tartare, Escargot bourguignon, Light chocolate mousse', '', 'Plat du Jour is the first standalone restaurant to be owned and managed by Swire Hotels. The 60-seat restaurant will be open for lunch and dinner daily and will offer authentic French regional cuisine. In Quarry Bay, finding a good restaurant to eat during lunch is not as easy as it sounds. Luckily, new restaurant Plat du Jour has appeared as a savior to offer up all your French favourites. Plat du Jour is a casual French trend with a bistro and is a little piece of Paris on Hoi Wan Street. It serves classic Simple french-western cuisine which included fish, poultry, pork, beef etc.,, designed by Aussie chef and consultant David Laris. Of course, you can also find Foie Gras, Escargot, Bouillabaisse, and Mussels. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit A, Quarry Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2812, 'en_US', 'China Tang', 'Come to China Tang and experience the most relaxed and comfortable and yet sumptuous and luxurious enjoyment of Chinese cuisines.', 'Signature Barbecued Pork, Braised e, fu Noodles with Scampi, Fried Rice with Whole Abalone', '', 'China Tang Restaurant, first opened in London in 2007 at the Dorchester Hotel, is opened in Hong Kong in November 2013 at LANDMARK ATRIUM. Also conceived and designed by Sir David Tang, China Tang offers the best of Chinese food within the most sumptuous and comfortable surroundings.The kitchen is led by a team of highly experienced Chinese chefs, offering the finest cuisines from Beijing, Sichuan and Canton. There is also an exceptional bar with a flexible private room in which the best and coldest drinks and cocktails are served, with the offer of dim sums and sweets throughout the day. All of our menus are printed in large prints so that there are no squinting or ambiguity over what are served. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2813, 'en_US', 'An Nam', 'A thoughtfully crafted creation of the exotic world of French Indochina, Ah Nam embodies the beauty and romance of times passed.', 'Steamed rice flan in Hue style, Wok, fried tamarind crab, An Nam signature king prawns', '', 'Affiliated with the well-established An Nam Group of Restaurants in Vietnam, An Nam in Hong Kong is well supported by extensive experience and expertise in authentic Vietnamese cuisine. A thoughtfully crafted creation of the exotic world of French Indochina, Ah Nam embodies the beauty and romance of times passed. Aiming to delight its guests with only the best culinary experiences, the Group’s expertise and creativity will surely bring the most genuine tastes of Vietnam to even the most discerning connoisseurs. An exceptional menu is presented alongside with popular Vietnamese cuisine. Favourites like pho and soft shell crab will be available with delicate Hué-style dishes such as unique and authentic banh beo (rice cake with dried shrimp) and cha gio (egg rolls). (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2814, 'en_US', 'I M Teppanyaki & Wine', 'Teppanyaki chef Lawrence Mok & his team make dining in Teppanyaki both a memorable and a unique experience.', 'Lobster with cream sauce, Foie gras with fruit and teriyaki sauce, A5 japanese premium beef 100g', '', 'Located in the heart of the Tung Lo Wan Road, Tai Hang, is the only recommended Teppanyaki restaurant in 2014-2015 Michelin Guide Hong Kong . Teppanyaki Chef Chan Mo Lin and his team will enable customers to \"Teppanyaki • Cast\" enjoys a unique and unforgettable experience. Mo Chan Lin is a Teppanyaki chef, had known for his past experience of working in five-star hotels and famous restaurants in Hong Kong while the other chefs, called him \"iron kitchen man.\" Mo master says the food is not only to feed their families, they should take care of the needs of a variety of senses, sight, taste, smell, touch, can be met. \"Teppanyaki • Cast\" at lunch time provides the selection of meal sets. Dinner time provides multi-channel package delicious dishes, also offers a variety of elaborate a la carte. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B, Tin Hau MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2815, 'en_US', 'Tapagria', 'TAPAGRIA is a glamorous tapas and sangria bar with the stunning night view in Hong Kong.', 'Slow, cooked crispy suckling pig, Sautéed Iberico chorizo with white wine, Daily Tapagria, style paella', '', 'Tapagri, with warm lighting and curved walls enveloping an intimate atmosphere encouraging inter-mingling, its curved wine bar hugs an open kitchen with charcoal grill oven, and a sumptuous outdoor lounge terrace opens out to the stunning skyline of Hong Kong. Tapagri’s ingredients are purchased from Spain to consist with high-quality agricultural products. For example, the variety of handmade cheese, is an addition to an array of classic Spanish vintages. Among unique design elements, the cosy people-friendly bar is floored with typical Spanish mosaic, We shall offer the largest and most exciting Sangria menu found in Asia, with exotic fruits and wine sourced from all corner of the globe. Meanwhile, dining chairs and bar stools are sculptural, paying homage to the legendary Catalan architect Gaudi. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2816, 'en_US', 'Sushi Mori (Circle Tower Branch)', 'Using only the best seasonal ingredients, all our itamaes are honed in serving our well acclaimed traditional Edomae-zushi.', 'Chef’s Mori Selection Sushi 12 pieces, Sea urchin roe', '', 'The theme colours of SUSHI MORI are gold, brown and pearl white. The image of bamboo forest as the main decorating motif brings an atmosphere of peace and elegance. The bar is made of original block of marble. There are 2 sets of counters with 4 and 6 seats separated by bamboo curtains. A relaxing individual room can be set at the other side of the restaurant for private parties and special occasions. The quality rice we choose is imported from Yamagata while 90% of other ingredients are daily collected from Hokkaido, Tokyo and Kyushu. We strive to bring the freshest, seasonal and authentic Edo Sushi to you.Our Chef keeps on making innovative Japanese cuisine for our guests and preparing high quality desserts in Japanese style for our guests as a perfect end of the meal. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit B, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2817, 'en_US', 'Sushi Mori (Causeway Bay Branch)', 'Using only the best seasonal ingredients, all our itamaes are honed in serving our well acclaimed traditional Edomae-zushi.', 'Chef’s Mori Selection Sushi 12 pieces, Sea urchin roe', '', 'The theme colours of SUSHI MORI are gold, brown and pearl white. The image of bamboo forest as the main decorating motif brings an atmosphere of peace and elegance. The bar is made of original block of marble. There are 2 sets of counters with 4 and 6 seats separated by bamboo curtains. A relaxing individual room can be set at the other side of the restaurant for private parties and special occasions. The quality rice we choose is imported from Yamagata while 90% of other ingredients are daily collected from Hokkaido, Tokyo and Kyushu. We strive to bring the freshest, seasonal and authentic Edo Sushi to you. In order to keep the high standards of our quality cuisine our Chef constantly improves his cooking methods. At the same time, he keeps on making innovative Japanese cuisine for our guests. Our Chef is keen on preparing high quality desserts in Japanese style for our guests as a perfect end of the meal. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2818, 'en_US', 'Liberty Exchange Kitchen & Bar', 'Liberty Exchange Kitchen is the perfect place for all-day dining with a wide range of international food selections.', 'Buttermilk Fried Cornish Hen with Organic Honey, Local Clams with Chorizo, Roasted Peppers and Rocket, Earl Grey Crème Brulee', '', 'The popular restaurant and bar Liberty Exchange Kitchen (LEX) is now divided into two floors, the ground on the first floor of the bar, offers a wide selection of drinks. Fine dining restaurant concept product, renamed Liberty kitchen locate the second floor. The restaurant has introduced a new menu, the change from a more friendly attitude of a true reflection, more importantly, the interior of the wood paneling adds, iron, leather interior, attention to detail found in the bundle of ropes and old lantern decorations, helps restaurant building the sense of New York food and wine which focuses on one kind of thought just the right fusion. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2819, 'en_US', 'Trattoria Queen Hollywood', 'Chefs of Trattoria Queen Hollywood are from Japan producing a high level of Italian dishes, plus the creative Japanese style with it.', 'Sauteed French Duck, Grilled Octopus with Garlic Mayonnaise, Premium Mussels Sake Spaghetti', '', 'Located at the junction of Queen Street and Hollywood Road\'s Trattoria Queen Hollywood, the main Italian bistro, but come along with fusion of Japanese taste, because the chef and manager are from Japanese.\nThe restaurant uses ingredients, 80% of the order from Italy. Decoration and menu are very simple, with walls painted with Italian and Japanese terrain. However, because of the food is at very satisfactory level, and store inside made a half semi-open kitchen, with former diners’ highly recommendation. So if you want to taste the cuisine with friends, we strongly recommend pre-booking inquiries. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2820, 'en_US', 'Iberico & Co.', 'Iberico & Co. is a famous Central SOHO district’s Spanish restaurant with the native taste of Spain.', 'Daily tortilla with tomato chutney, Jamon iberico, Spicy chorizo and chicken paella', '', 'Iberico & Co. is a famous Central SOHO district’s Spanish restaurant, the location is just in the second part of the Central–Mid-Levels escalator and walkway system. The restaurant is just very close to the escalator, it is very easy to find and convenient. This restaurant serves mainly Spanish cuisine, and is very popular with foreigners, often filled with diners every night at eight o’clock, so you might need to previously book a table and it would be more secure to have seats. Loomingly in the restaurant lights, the space has created a mysterious atmosphere. Although the tables and chairs are arranged dense, but very suitable for about a group of friends or colleagues after work to chat and enjoy a Spanish-style meal. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit C, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2821, 'en_US', 'Fatty Crab', 'Fatty Crab brings its popular take on the best of South East Asian flavours to Hong Kong.', 'Chilli crab, Crispy pork and watermelon salad', '', 'After receiving numerous awards and accolades in New York, which include a listing in the Michelin Guide’s list of Bib Gourmand Restaurants and glowing New York Times reviews for its various concepts, Fatty Crab brings its popular take on the best of South East Asian flavours to Hong Kong. This neighbourhood joint serves Zakary Pelaccio’s bold take on Malaysian, Thai, Indonesian, Vietnamese and Singaporean inspired cuisine -- while using western style cooking techniques. Signature dishes include Chili Crab, Watermelon Pickle & Crispy Pork, Fatty Duck, and ‘Cue Smoked Ribs. All condiments and pastes are made in-house from scratch, with love…a lotta love. The bar at Fatty Crab offers a unique hand crafted cocktail list created by our own bartenders, with help of Fatty Crew’s very own mixologist, Phillip Ward, who has experience in numerous, noteworthy, New York establishments such as Mayahuel, Death & Co, Pegu Club and Flatiron Lounge. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit C, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2822, 'en_US', 'Qi House of Sichuan', 'Come to Qi and experience a new concept of intense flavours of spicy, aromatic, sweet, bitter, sour, peppery, and salty that you taste in our culinary selection.', 'Mouth watering chicken, Cumin lamb with roasted chilli, Chilli Dungeness crab', '', 'The name Qi (pronounced: chee) is defined as a shining star and inspired by one of the fundamental ingredients in Sichuan cuisine - the star anise. The Chinese character, ancient in its roots, is formed by the characters of water and mouth - reflective of the mouth watering flavours of Sichuan food.Our team of chefs, with their deep rooted experience in Sichuan cuisine, has created a modern interpretation of traditional and authentic Sichuan dishes that reflect the “seven flavours of Sichuan” (spicy, aromatic, sweet, bitter, sour, peppery, and salty). We hope you savour the spectrum of intense flavours that you will experience here. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit B2, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2823, 'en_US', 'Wagyu Takumi', 'It brings to the table Seiromushi - the traditional steaming of the freshest fine ingredients. It forms a healthy mix of textures and flavours that are subtle and delicate.', 'Charcoal Grilled Wagyu Beef', '', 'With the simple yet pre-eminent decor, Gin Sai delivers a contemporary Kyoto feel with a well-balanced play of muted palette of dark browns. From the Japanese Kyoto embroidery door of the 16-seat room to the tableware sourced from different parts of Japan, these all exhibit excellent attention to details, the distinctive characteristic of Gin Sai. Headed by Chef Ogawa, Gin Sai serves premium Japanese cooked food. It brings to the table Seiromushi - the traditional steaming of the freshest fine ingredients such as Wagyu beef, fresh seafood, Kurobuta pork and seasonal vegetables, without any seasoning. It forms a healthy mix of textures and flavours that are subtle and delicate. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A3, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2824, 'en_US', 'Rozan', 'By using only the freshest fish that is available today the chef changes the menu daily so that each visit is a unique experience.', 'Omakase', '', 'Rozan is the most prestigious sushi restaurant in town. An intriguing escape from the bustle of the city. Serving a select clientele of 12 diners at a luxury fragrant cypress wood counter you will enjoy the exquisite Japanese sushi that only a sushi master with 25 years experience can create. By using only the freshest fish that is available today the chef changes the menu daily so that each visit is a unique experience. Rozan is a sensation to be shared with your closest friends.Rozan is open for lunch and dinner. One day advance booking is recommended. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit A3, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2825, 'en_US', 'Stone Nullah Tavern', 'Stone Nullah Tavern offer New American Comfort Food, Liquor Bar & Kitchen', 'Maple Bacon, Pig\'s Head Nachos, Smoked Cauliflower', '', 'As a liquor bar and kitchen, we serve New American Fare in a 70-seat Tavern, with a selection of American craft beers on tap as well as a wide boutique selection of whiskies, rums and rare bourbons smuggled straight from Kentucky. Partner and Chef Vinny Lauria interprets classic American food utilising ingredients from local organic farms and draws inspiration from his travels throughout Asia. Stone Nullah Lane is steeped in history. Directly across the street from Stone Nullah Tavern, is the Grade 1 Historical Building, the “Blue House”. Built in the early 20th it is one of only a handful of pre-war tenements that has been preserved. Its distinctive colour was a result of surplus blue paint from the government during its 1920\'s renovation. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A3, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2826, 'en_US', 'Torimen', 'A contemporary yakitori & ramen restaurant that celebrates authentic Japanese palates.', 'Ebi Ramen, Minced chicken stick stuffed with cheese, Grilled oyster with nori risotto', '', 'At Torimen, not only we strive to maintain high quality standard of food & beverage, but we always remember to excite our customers\' palate. When the traditional emulsified tonkotsu soup base meets Torimen\'s own creation – infused ebi essence, an irresistible aroma and taste infuses through your five senses. We insist on NO MSG in order to let our customers indulge in the genuine tastes of our fresh ingredients. Torimen believes that a remarkable bowl of ramen should start from the most primitive ingredient – water. Regular water can easily eliminate the genuine taste of fresh ingredients, therefore Torimen carefully picks PH 8.6 water to make its tonkotsu and infused ebi essence in order to secure genuine taste of all ingredients, making every sip and bite unforgettable. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2827, 'en_US', 'Ronin', 'RŌNIN is a Japanese inspired dining bar focus on fish and seafood and over 100 curated selection of wine.', 'Uni, Fresh Nori, Aonori Panko, Kagoshima beef, Market Fish Karaage with Yuzu Kosho Mayo', '', 'RŌNIN is a Japanese inspired dining bar with a focus on fish and seafood and a curated selection of Japanese Whisky, sake, shochu, beer, wine and unique cocktails.　The RŌNIN food menu varies day-to-day depending on the selection of fresh market products available. We offer a chef’s tasting menu as well as an à la carte menu. RŌNIN has a diverse and growing Japanese Whisky collection. The Whisky menu features over 100 varieties from more than 10 distilleries and many of the bottles are exclusively available at RŌNIN. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2828, 'en_US', 'Tamarind Pan-Asian Restaurant & Bar', 'Best of Indian/Pakistani, Thai, Vegetarian and Vietnamese Cuisines', 'Tamarind Cod Fish, Stir fried spicy pork neck, Lamb Dum Biryani', '', 'Tamarind (venue previously known as Viceroy) restaurant satisfies all your senses from offering a veritable feast for your taste-buds to providing a spectacular sight from its outdoor terrace. The fabulous new Pan-Asian restaurant is located in Wanchai, facing Hong Kong\'s spectacular skyline. Serving the best of Thai, Indian and Vietnamese cuisine, the restaurant is perfect for lunch, dinner or drinks. The spacious, vibrant restaurant features two main dining rooms (Sugar Room & Spice Room) that seats up to 150 guests, welcoming and functional for large scale events. The warm interiors set an ambient setting for those romantic dinners right by the water. The outdoor space is overlooking Hong Kong\'s stunning skyline, with lounge seating area, making it a perfect place for drinks. The relaxed atmosphere will make your guests fit right into place. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A1, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2830, 'en_US', 'Yun Yan', 'Yun Yan combines unconventional cooking styles and updated classic Sichuan recipes from fresh local ingredients.', 'Seared crab claws with pickled chilli sauce, Poached Mandarin fish slices layered with crispy soya beans, Crispy chicken dices with spicy dried red chillies and Sichuan peppercorns', '', 'Authentic Sichuan cooking takes on a new identity with an array of creative dishes that attract today’s those who enjoy this fiery yet highly nuanced cuisine. Yun Yan combines unconventional cooking styles and updated classic Sichuan recipes to create dishes that evoke surprise and smiles, coupled with an attentive and knowledgeable service team that makes lunch or dinner at Yun Yan the place to be. Sichuan cuisine’s huge variety of tastes has won the praise of – “One dish, one style; a hundred dishes, a hundred tastes”. Combining the richness of traditional Sichuan flavors and modern technique, Yun Yan exemplifies the five distinctive spicy tastes in Sichuan cuisine: Mala, Hula, Pickled Pepper, Chopped Chili and Hot & Sour; and the non-spicy specialties of Salty, Sweet & Sour, taking diners on a gourmet journey through Sichuan. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit A, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2831, 'en_US', 'French Window Brasserie and Bar', 'Here the service is responsive with a friendly staff ready to assist in explaining all the dishes and ingredients.', 'Seafood platter, Crunchy suckling pig with matchstick potatoes, French lemon pie topped with meringue', '', 'The taste of Parisian bistro cooking awaits diners at French Window Brasserie and Bar, one of the Mira Dining’s European eateries. Fresh ingredients from France are prepared using modern French techniques in an atmosphere of casual, lively bonhomme all set amidst the clean and modern surroundings. For those who enjoy food in Hong Kong, this is a place for a little romance and good times; a celebration of ‘joie de vivre’ with the French. From a host of seafood dishes to a menu of entrées that includes brasserie items like Poached duck torchon, steamed mussels in white wine and so much more, French Window Brasserie and Bar is a European venue for those who want to try Parisian-style eating. The menu is fun and designed for sharing. It features a host of traditional French comfort food like Coq au vin, Beef bourguignon and others. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2832, 'en_US', 'Cuisine Cuisine (Central Branch)', 'Mastering the 36 Cooking Methods in Chinese cuisine, the Master Chef of Cuisine Cuisine ifc offers a genuine Cantonese dining.', 'Sautéed crystal king prawn, Braised abalone served on fresh mushroom and vegetables, Stewed whole tomato stuffed with mixed fungus', '', 'Situated in the city\'s most prestigious business district at ifc mall, Cuisine Cuisine ifc is regarded as a “tycoon canteen” and the best place for a classy and elegant dining experience. After a meticulous refurbishment in 2014, the restaurant has reopened with a new look that showcases new carpet with an auspicious carp motif; and decorative red ink wash paintings silhouetted against the its iconic scripts of 36 cooking methods on the wall.The newly refurbished restaurant offers seating for more than 200 guests and an extended view of Kowloon skyline from the main dining hall. With double-height ceiling and huge glass windows, Cuisine Cuisine ifc and its three private rooms immerse the guests in sweeping panoramic views of Hong Kong and stunning views of festive fireworks displays, as well as the daily display of “A Symphony of Lights” show. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2833, 'en_US', 'Tsui Hang Village (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'Each dish is prepared with select ingredients and sauces that represent real Guangdong cooking.', 'Crispy Minced Carp Cakes and Crispy Bread Topped with Milk Custard, Honey glazed barbecued pork, Fried King Prawns in Mango Sauce Topped with Caviar', '', 'For nearly 40 years, Tsui Hang Village Restaurant has been a place for those who enjoy Cantonese cooking. Currently, three outlets in Hong Kong feature classic recipes and local favorite dishes, keeping regulars coming back for more while the Tsui Hang name continues to attract new fans every day. Over the years, Tsui Hang Village is dedicated to preserving the traditions of hand-crafted Guangzhou cuisine with relaxing atmosphere and attentive service. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2834, 'en_US', 'Tsui Hang Village (Causeway Bay Branch)', 'Each dish is prepared with select ingredients and sauces that represent real Guangdong cooking.', 'Crispy minced carp cakes and bread topped with milk custard, Honey glazed barbecued prok, Assorted fruit and meat platter', '', 'For nearly 40 years, Tsui Hang Village Restaurant has been a place for those who enjoy Cantonese cooking. Currently, three outlets in Hong Kong feature classic recipes and local favorite dishes, keeping regulars coming back for more while the Tsui Hang name continues to attract new fans every day. Over the years, Tsui Hang Village is dedicated to preserving the traditions of hand-crafted Guangzhou cuisine with relaxing atmosphere and attentive service. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit A, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2835, 'en_US', 'Tsui Hang Village (Central Branch)', 'Each dish is prepared with select ingredients and sauces that represent real Guangdong cooking.', 'Wok, seared sea bass in premium soy sauce, Shredded boneless chicken, Fried rice with conpoy, dried fish and roasted duck meat', '', 'For nearly 40 years, Tsui Hang Village Restaurant has been a place for those who enjoy Cantonese cooking. Currently, three outlets in Hong Kong feature classic recipes and local favorite dishes, keeping regulars coming back for more while the Tsui Hang name continues to attract new fans every day. Over the years, Tsui Hang Village is dedicated to preserving the traditions of hand-crafted Guangzhou cuisine with relaxing atmosphere and attentive service. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2836, 'en_US', 'Assaggio Trattoria Italiana (Wan Chai Branch)', 'Manage to satisfy both discriminating diners as well as more down-to-earth people who know about traditional Italian fare.', 'Pan, seared Sea bass, White Wine Sauce, Sliced Veal, Tuna Sauce, Beetroot & Celery, Homemade Cantucci Biscuits', '', 'A new form of modern Italian dining, Assaggio Trattoria Italiana offers a place where diners can come together in a relaxed and collegial atmosphere to taste trattoria-style fare served in that special la dolce vita ambience. Fresh ingredients like authentic Italian flour, olive oil and cheeses go into every Assaggio dish making this restaurant a representative taste of Italy. The rustic and welcoming atmosphere is complemented by a spectacular terrace that overlooks Victoria Harbour and a private room that makes you feel at home. While being a nice getaway and alfresco dining spot that pleasantly caters to your needs, the menu of Assaggio Trattoria Italiana features a range of handmade pasta as well as Ospitalità Italiana qualified ingredients imported straight from Italy. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit C, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2837, 'en_US', 'Assaggio Trattoria Italiana (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'Manage to satisfy both discriminating diners as well as more down-to-earth people who know about traditional Italian fare.', 'Seafood Salad, Casarecce Pasta, Rocket Leave, Pesto & Black Truffle, Rum Chocolate Pudding with Red Berries', '', 'A new form of modern Italian dining, Assaggio Trattoria Italiana offers a place where diners can come together in a relaxed and collegial atmosphere to taste trattoria-style fare served in that special la dolce vita ambience. Fresh ingredients like authentic Italian flour, olive oil and cheeses go into every Assaggio dish making this restaurant a representative taste of Italy. The rustic and welcoming atmosphere is complemented by a spectacular terrace that overlooks Victoria Harbour and a private room that makes you feel at home. While being a nice getaway and alfresco dining spot that pleasantly caters to your needs, the menu of Assaggio Trattoria Italiana features a range of handmade pasta as well as Ospitalità Italiana qualified ingredients imported straight from Italy. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2838, 'en_US', 'Saboten Japanese Cutlet (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'Specially-bred mature pigs and barley-fed come together to create a pork product that’s a bit sweeter and tenderer than you might find anywhere else.', 'Pork Tenderloin with Radish, Pork Tenderloin and Shrimp, Hot Miso over Pork Loin with spring Onion', '', 'The stylishly-appointed Saboten in Tsimshatsui showcases the love for traditional Japanese architectural style that draws on the red, wood colors and hemp rope curtain to set the tone. Guest may sit back and relax on the earth-tone sofa and booth seats while overlooking the dynamic city life through glass windows; or simply enjoy the intimacy and spaciousness inside the semi-private room meticulously zoned by the rope curtain. You have choice at Saboten between tenderloin with less fat and the whiter, firmer loin, which makes the good cut for conventional Tonkatsu dishes. Specially-bred mature pigs and barley-fed come together to create a pork product that’s a bit sweeter and tenderer than you might find anywhere else. Added to this are the sauces and condiments that make a Saboten Tonkatsu an irresistible place to dine out. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit B2, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2839, 'en_US', 'Saboten Japanese Cutlet (Causeway Bay Branch)', 'Specially-bred mature pigs and barley-fed come together to create a pork product that’s a bit sweeter and tenderer than you might find anywhere else.', 'Premium Pork Tenderloin Set, Pork Mille, Feuille and Pork Tenderloin Roll Combo, Pork Tenderloin with Radish', '', 'Saboten in Causeway Bay welcomes diners with a traditional Japanese dining room atmosphere featuring clean, crisp all wood freshness. The venue features flexible seating to accommodate different sizes of groups all set in a comfortable atmosphere. For lunch or dinner, Saboten offers an interesting Japanese Tonkatsu-style dining like no other. You have choice at Saboten between tenderloin with less fat and the whiter, firmer loin, which makes the good cut for conventional Tonkatsu dishes. Specially-bred mature pigs and barley-fed come together to create a pork product that’s a bit sweeter and tenderer than you might find anywhere else. Added to this are the sauces and condiments that make a Saboten Tonkatsu an irresistible place to dine out. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2840, 'en_US', 'Three Monkeys', 'Three Monkeys is an IZAKAYA themed Japanese restaurant & bar specializing in yakitori and a delicious range of homestyle food.', 'Belly Wraps, Prime Rib Steak, Grilled Ox, tongue', '', 'Three Monkeys is an IZAKAYA themed Japanese restaurant & bar specializing in yakitori and a delicious range of homestyle food located on Hollywood Road, three monkeys is a Izakaya Japanese themed restaurant and bar specializes in yakitori and a variety of delicious family-style restaurants. Stopping by Three Monkeys to taste every dish you happen to find a distinct Japanese flavor, adding modern elements to the unique traditional cuisine. Three Monkeys’s menu is full of Japanese cuisine, including yakitori, a unique classic recipes, as well as wide range of cocktails directory. Each dish is ideal fusion for sharing a cocktail or a bottle of sake, you can fully enjoy the feeling the well-made crossover food and wine. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2841, 'en_US', 'AMMO', '“AMMO”, a slang term for ammunition, is also an acronym for Asia, Modern, Museum and Original, effectively communicating the overall culinary and dining experience.', 'Buffalo Mozzarella Panna Cotta, Sea Urchin and roman zucchini sauce, Slow Cook Egg with Toro', '', 'Dining in heritage and history, AMMO, a restaurant and bar, opens at the new Asia Society Hong Kong Center in Admiralty. In a setting unmatched anywhere in Hong Kong, AMMO draws inspiration from the historical, architectural and cultural significance of its location. A former explosives magazine compound created by the British army in the mid-19th century, the site underwent a conversion by renowned New York-based architects Tod Williams and Billie Tsien and is now the Asia Society Hong Kong Center. “AMMO”, a slang term for ammunition, is also an acronym for Asia, Modern, Museum and Original, effectively communicating the overall culinary and dining experience. The phrase acknowledges the café’s Asian roots and identity, its thoroughly modern continental cuisine, its unquestionably unique position within a heritage landmark museum, and its original concept. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit F, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2843, 'en_US', 'Bistro Du Vin', 'The charming eatery serves an array of authentic dishes from all across France.', 'Slow Cooked Lamb Shank in Tomato Sauce, Duck Leg Confit, Charcuterie Platter', '', 'Bistro du Vin opened towards the end of 2009 to deliver a truly authentic French bistro dining experience. The charming eatery serves an array of authentic dishes from all across France. They are prepared from traditional recipes with the freshest ingredients, but without the fuss and pomp typically associated with French fine-dining. A simple yet comprehensive selection of wines is also available at friendly prices – by the bottle, by the glass or carafé. At Bistro du Vin, guests enjoy convivial service while taking in a slice of the French way of life through the music and memorabilia decorating the walls. Bistro du Vin’s first restaurant is at Shaw Centre, Orchard. Another outlet has since opened on Zion Road, opposite Great World City. Bistro du Vin has also been replicated in Hong Kong, along with our recently opened seafood bistro Le Port Parfumé. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit C, Kennedy Town MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2844, 'en_US', 'Wild Grass', 'This is the real food the way it should be - fresh, organic, ingredients prepared simply.', 'Homemade liver parfait served with crusty country bread and tart piccalilli, 5hrs Stewed beef shin, clove, steamed goat cheese dumpling', '', 'We are all about natural, sustainable ingredients, lovingly prepared by traditional slow cooking methods. Here at Wild Grass, you will find wholesome, time-honored recipes, adapted for a new generation of food lover. We exclusively serve OBE beef, a wild organic cattle that roams freely, grazing on grass in the open pastures of the Australian outback. We’re proud to serve OBE beef - wild, organic cattle that roams freely, grazing on grass in over 7 million hectares of open pastures in the Australia Outback. This beef is truly a cut above, come and taste the difference. All our produce is organic and sourced from sustainable supplies in the UK, France, Australia, New Zealand and Hong Kong certified organic farms. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2845, 'en_US', 'Jang', 'Traditional Korean dishes with homemade sauce, “Jang,” influenced by new techniques with chefs from Korea.', 'Spicy beef potato soup, Korean Style Beef Carpaccio, Korean Fried Chicken', '', 'Food has become so important in our lives where some say, \"You live to eat; not eat to live.\" At Jang, we want you to think of this phrase on every visit. Jang is the first Korean restaurant in Hong Kong to serve high quality, modern Korean cuisine. Every person who has eaten at Korean BBQ restaurants would understand the smell and poor quality of service – we will be the first one to change that. Korean cuisine was never viewed as low quality cooking until it transformed into what it is now in foreign countries. At Jang, we would like to share the new experience of providing top class food and culture at the right price. We serve traditional Korean dishes with homemade sauce, “Jang,” influenced by new techniques with chefs from Korea. Jang’s goal is to become the first Korean restaurant to change the image of Korean food abroad and to be the best Korean restaurant in Hong Kong. We would like to welcome you to experience this exciting change together. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2846, 'en_US', 'Giando Italian Restaurant & Bar', 'Delivering and preparing simple authentic Italian dishes from premium quality ingredients, much of which comes directly from Italy.', 'Beef Carpaccio with Argula and Parmigiano in Balsamic Vinegar, truffles pizza, Strozzapreti Di Pasta Fresca Allo Scoglio', '', 'Gianni Caprioli, former helmsman of a renowned Italian restaurant, has struck out on his own to bring Hong Kong a true taste of Italy. Located on the first floor of the Fleet Arcade, Fenwick Pier, this elegant restaurant commands an impressive view of Hong Kong skyline. It has offered its patrons a unique gastronomic experience since opening its doors in September 2012. Giando restaurant is envisioned as a minimalist, classic Italian dining experience, and the restaurant’s interiors came together under the direction of Chef Gianni. He says that the focus is primarily on the food, which makes excellent use of freshly imported Italian produce. His unwavering commitment to excellence means that diners can expect a standout experience on all fronts – from the culinary offerings and extensive selection of wines that are imported directly from Italy as well as coming from Gianni’s own collection of historic and iconic wines, to exquisite international service and, of course, the one-of-a-kind vista. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2847, 'en_US', 'Restoration', 'Come relax and enjoy the revival of soul warming food, libations and traditions in a setting that is unlike any other in Hong Kong.', 'BBQ RIBS, Duck Confit Salad, Bacon Cheese Burger', '', 'New Orleans has an addictive effect on those who\'ve been there, bestowing creole cuisine and southern hospitality with intoxicating charm. We want to share our love for the Big Easy by bringing a piece of it to you. Come relax and enjoy the revival of soul warming food, libations and traditions in a setting that is unlike any other in Hong Kong. We are purveyors of robust flavors, reinvigorated recipes, alluring service, and funky refurbished style. Join us in what we lovingly refer to as our \"home\' for an experience that will transport you to a city that holds our hearts - probably because they are in our stomachs。 (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2848, 'en_US', 'Island Tang', 'Island Tang serving all the standard Cantonese dishes prepared in a classical traditional way and offering Chinese haute cuisine.', 'Scrambled egg white with imperial bird\'s nest, Signature roasted chicken, Steamed shrimp dumplings', '', 'Island Tang is a luxurious Hong Kong Cafe serving all the standard Cantonese dishes prepared in a classical traditional way and offering Chinese haute cuisine - with classical dishes with abalone and shark\'s fin, superbly prepared by Island Tang\'s experienced chef. The decorations in Island Tang are done by Sir David Tang and place emphasis on a total sense of comport and an understated sense of luxury. There will be no difference on what will be ordered from the comprehensive menu ranging from something as basic as wonton noodles to Yoshihama Abalone. Island Tang has 4 private rooms, each equipped with LCD Television and IT presentation facilities. Three of these private rooms are interconnected and can form one larger private room. In the main dining area, there is a fashionable bar and an unparalleled cellar of fine wines of exceptional vintages. \"Customer is King\" is the motto and belief of Island Tang and will be firmly remembered and executed by each experienced culinary and service team. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit K, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2849, 'en_US', 'Kowloon Tang', 'Kowloon Tang is a s restaurant erving authentic Cantonese cuisine and rural country food.', 'Scrambled egg white with imperial bird\'s nest, Signature roasted chicken, Steamed shrimp dumplings', '', 'Located in Element in the heart of Tsim Sha Tsui, Kowloon Tang is a newly opened restaurant serving authentic Cantonese cuisine and rural country food. Being the sister restaurant of Island Tang, the one Michelin-starred eatery offering Chinese haute cuisine and all the standard Cantonese dishes, Kowloon Tang is guaranteed to provide another high level of service and food quality. The design idea of Kowloon Tang is contributed by Sir David Tang who got inspiration from Art Deco design style. The restaurant has three private rooms. They can be booked for private parties or business purposes. With high ceiling and elegant decoration, the private rooms give a sense of luxury. The main dining room is decorated with more traditional Chinese accessories, such as the calligraphic couplets. There is an outdoor dining area offering customers an additional choice. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C2, Kowloon MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2850, 'en_US', 'Ista – The Curry Place', 'Passionate Indian cuisine in a luxurious setting in the heart of the City.', 'Lamp chop with ginger, Chicken tikka marinated in green chili paste, Potatoes stuffed with assorted nuts', '', 'Located in Lan Kwai Fong, in the heart of Central, Ista proudly brings you their passionate Indian Cuisine in a luxurious setting. It offers a unique combination of ambience and elegance to create a truly delightful dining experience. Ista’s menu offers an array of Indian street-food favourites, tapas-style appetizers, curries, biryani and desserts satisfying the most discerning palates. It also offers an extensive menu for Catering and Delivery orders. Equipped with many unique features such as Havana Terrace and private dining area, Ista is an ideal place for corporate lunches, birthday parties, cocktail parties and any other special occasion. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2851, 'en_US', 'Ganga\'s Fine Indian Cuisine', 'Head Chef Suresh Babu continues to create a royal array of authentic Indian dishes from his menu designed with decades of research and experience.', 'Lamb tikka Anghar, Chicken chettinad, Kerala fish curry', '', 'We were launched by P.S. Ganga in 1988 on Wyndham Street of Hong Kong Island as one of the only three restaurants in the area. We boast of being a truly local restaurant that introduced fine Indian cuisine in the neighbourhood as well as setting the trend for Wyndham Street as one of the main hubs of HK\'s food and beverage industry. As Mr Ganga retired, he decided to hand over the reigns of his creation to his son Sanjay, who made the executive decision to change the name of the restaurant to Ganga\'s to honour his father and his legacy. Mr. Sanjay maintains the passion for highest quality ingredients, immaculate cooking, extensive wine list and service with a smile that results in a stellar dining experience. Head Chef Suresh Babu who has been with us for more than 19 years, continues to create a royal array of authentic Indian dishes from his menu designed with decades of research and experience. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2852, 'en_US', 'Suzuike Japanese Cuisine', 'A casual dining experience is often more enjoyable, especially when you just want to enjoy a good meal.', 'Foie gras sushi, Wagyu Beef, Bisque', '', 'Suzuike understated elegance, \"Suzuike\" word is in a sharp light-colored marble marbled walls, from a pragmatic gray stone door. Put your hand on the door handle black wooden pillars in the middle, the door will magically slide open, simple and polished decor, and spacing out the table clean color scheme. Everything is well thought out to provide a comfortable, relaxed dining experience. A quiet and secluded restaurant nowadays more and more popular, the restaurant put more focus on what is important, the food! A casual dining experience is often more enjoyable, especially when you just want to enjoy a good meal, leave the hustle and bustle outside the stone door. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit C, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2853, 'en_US', 'La Villa', 'LaVilla TST offers a diversified range of food going from French to Italian and German snacks specialized in seafood and grills.', 'Cold seafood platter, Cream of wild mushroom with black truffle oil, Grilled US prime rib, eye with French fries and red wine sauce', '', 'Located in Tsim Sha Tsui, have an open night out in LaVillaTST with an extended patio disposed right along the Victoria Harbour. LaVilla TST offers a diversified range of food going from French to Italian and German snacks too. Specialized in Seafood and Grills, We believe in getting the finest ingredients in order to realize the best culinary confection as possible. Our products have all been imported, in order to make your fine dining experience an unforgettable moment. Also, there will have a Bar Scene at night, please indulging in our hottest live band performance. We would like to welcome you to our first private outlet, designed exclusively for our VIPs in order to introduce them, and to you of course, a new trend, a new style, a different approach. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit P2, East Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2854, 'en_US', 'Sun Tung Lok Chinese Cuisine (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'SUN TUNG LOK Chinese Cuisine, focuses on top quality Guangdong cuisine and tailor made customer services have leaded our restaurant to an unparalleled reputation in the market.', 'Steamed glutinousrice with freshchickenand mushroom onlotus leaf, Sliced beef with assorted mushrooms in abalone sauce, Fried rice with Chinese preserved meat', '', 'SUN TUNG LOK Chinese Cuisine was founded in 1969 by the Yuen\'s family. In the last four decades, our focuses on top quality Guangdong cuisine and tailor made customer services have leaded our restaurant to an unparalleled reputation in the market. In 2011, SUN TUNG LOK Chinese Cuisine was named a MICHELIN 3 Stars restaurant by the famous gourmet dining guide. It became the first non-hotel eatery to be rewarded 3 stars in Hong Kong. In addition, we are one of only two Chinese restaurants in the world to receive such recognition. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
