(2856, 'en_US', 'Edo & Bibo', 'edo & bibo offers a menu that is tantalizing and delightful, serving premium oysters, fresh seafood and the finest cut steak.', 'Beef Tartare with Italian Black Truffle, Blue Mussels, Black Truffle Scrambled Eggs', '', 'In Latin, “edo” means eat and “bibo” means drink. At edo & bibo we bring together all the elements that discerning guests love about the culinary experience. Unlike any oyster bars, edo & bibo offers a menu that is tantalizing and delightful, serving premium oysters, fresh seafood and the finest cut steak. edo & bibo offers a menu that is tantalizing and delightful, serving premium oysters, fresh seafood and the finest cut steak. Our extraordinary food, notable wine list, quality service and exquisite atmosphere is the ultimate culinary experience. Edo & bibo offers a semi buffet during lunch and a full a la carte menu during dinner. Our chefs serve up the finest oysters from Japan’s Kumamoto to Europe’s Belon, and best cuts from Qumiushi Wagyu Tomahawk Steak to Spanish Iberico Pork. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit F2, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2857, 'en_US', 'The Monogamous Chinese', 'The Monogamous Chinese menu offers authentic and reworked fare that elevates the taste and experience of each serving.', 'Deep fried shrimp spring rolls with sweet and sour Sauce, Crispy pork spare ribs in our house black vinegar sauce, Poached sliced beef in hot chili oil', '', 'The latest upscale restaurant to grace Hong Kong’s SoHo district exudes the spices and flavours of China’s Sichuan province and of the country’s capital Beijing. The Monogamous Chinese specialises in authentic Sichuan and Peking recipes made from genuine imported ingredients from the provinces. Owners, Chefs Shizh Hoi Ping and restaurateur Jamie Higgins, have come together to combine their cooking and restaurant service experience to develop contemporary and sophisticated Chinese fine-dining set in a tastefully modern restaurant environment. This translates into the kitchen with the chefs staying true to the fidelity of the ingredients and traditions of the dishes marrying this with their own experiences in preparing excellent contemporary cuisine for modern diners. All sauces and spices are prepared in-house from the best seasonal produce under the direction of Chef Shizh Hoi Ping. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit D1, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2858, 'en_US', '1968 Indonesian Restaurant', '1968 Indonesian Restaurant is a decent place for Indonesian cuisine, and suitable tastes for Hong Konger.', 'Ox tail soup, Laksa Noodle, Hainan Chicken', '', 'If you love Indonesian cuisine, 1968 Indonesian Restaurant is your place. It is very wide and can accommodate hundreds of people dining. Indonesia is also quite authentic decor features traditional simple elegance, and then lined with modern decor, stylish people a sense of comfort to the elegance. 1968 Indonesian Restaurant within the area of L Place is similar to other restaurants around, with stylish modern decor, there are many types of seating areas, such as the two little tables romantic date, or it seems like a small roadside kiosk tall seating area, or You can do a big birthday party table area, and very different from traditional Indonesian restaurant. Indonesian satay, most emphatically is that the sauce can be said that the whole delicacy’s soul. Traditional Indian taste very strong, so the kitchen’s chef adjusts a little taste for Hong Kong residents, the concentration and the degree of fine-tuning incense, so the taste is more suitable for the tastes of Hong Kong. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2859, 'en_US', 'REI', 'REI offers teppanyaki a la carte and also as set menus. Enjoy your meal and the theatre of teppanyaki amongst the backdrop of stunning harbour views.', 'Rei assorted sushi platter, Assorted tempura, Sauteed Japanese wagyu beef with komiyaki sauce', '', 'Since 2003, REI has been serving sushi and sashimi made from fresh, imported ingredients, as well as a wide array of Japanese dishes. The warm décor and wooden furniture throughout the restaurant reflects its authenticity as a traditional and cosy Japanese eatery. Eight grand lights with a morning-glory-shaped crown command the attention of diners stepping into the restaurant. REI offers teppanyaki a la carte and also as set menus. Enjoy your meal and the theatre of teppanyaki amongst the backdrop of stunning harbour views. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2860, 'en_US', 'The Boathouse', 'THE BOATHOUSE is of high quality of food, wide variety of cuisines, friendly and efficient service.', 'Bucket of fresh seafood (mussels served with white wine garlic cream sauce), Fish & chips, Tandoori swordfish', '', 'The Boathouse, the 3-storey building overlooking Stanley Bay is one of seafront spot\'s most popular dining landmarks. Steeped in a stylish East Coast flavour reminiscent of Martha\'s Vineyard, the relaxed décor offers a comfortable and casual environment. An international a-la-carte menu features the freshest seafood, appetizers, salads and dishes from African Chicken, Tandoori Swordfish to Barbequed Baby Back Pork Ribs. The Spinnaker\'s Bar on the ground floor offers a comprehensive selection of beers, wines and cocktails. The Boathouse belongs to Cafe Deco Group, which is one of Hong Kong\'s leading and most successful bar and restaurant groups. The success behind the group lies in its full dining experience for all, including consistently high quality of food, wide variety of cuisines, friendly and efficient service, as well as appealing ambience of its outlets for any occasion, business or pleasure. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', 'Taxi or buses from Central', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2861, 'en_US', 'Shanghai Garden Restaurant', 'The restaurant offers a tranquil ambience as well as the authentic flavors of Shanghai and Huai Yang cuisine.', 'Deep, fried sliced fish with sweet and sour sauce, Zhenjang pork, Sautéed Shelled Shrimps', '', 'Shanghai Garden is located at Hutchison House, Central. With a vibrant and lively atmosphere, the restaurant offers a tranquil ambience as well as the authentic flavors of Shanghai and Huai Yang cuisine. Shanghai cuisine is characterized by a heavy use of oils, sugar and sauces, hence a richness of flavour and colour. The usual culinary techniques employed include braising with brown sauce, simmering, slip-frying and sauteing. Subsequently Shanghaiese dishes are noted for their balance of sweetness and saltiness, oily without being greasy. Famous Shanghai dishes include stir-fried eel in brown sauce, steamed meat and soup dumplings, and sauteed shrimps. Serving with tailor-made European style tableware and containers, guests may choose their favorite dishes from a superb la carte menu. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(2862, 'en_US', 'Wooloomooloo Prime (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'Wooloomooloo Prime presents the serious steak lover with the next level of our fine beef selection.', 'Yellowfin tuna and spanner crab tartare, Australian wagyu tomahawk, Beef wellington', '', 'Wooloomooloo Group has served sizzling premium steaks and time-honored favorites with the freshest ingredients and passion since 2004. As an established member of Hong Kong’s grill house circle, we have developed three successful brands, Wooloomooloo Prime, Wooloomooloo Steakhouse and The Chop House, at prominent locations in Hong Kong and Singapore. Using first-rate fresh produce cooked with care and an experienced hand, our menu is inspired by the representation of real flavor and our passion for great food. Within the cozy and contemporary décor of our restaurants, you will find a professional staff serving a delightful meal in an intimate, welcoming atmosphere. As we expand our presence in greater Asia, Wooloomooloo Group provides the backdrop for all occasions from corporate events to moments of celebration. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
