(3445, 'en_US', 'The Helenia home bistro', 'The Helenia home bistro welcome you to the real flavor of sous vide cooking.', 'Helenia Smoke Bacon Pesto Linguine, Norway Chill Salmon with Fresh Herbs', '', 'The Helenia home bistro welcome you to the real flavor of sous vide cooking. A cozy romantic atmosphere around our busy water oven as you watch our passionate chefs prepare the freshest ingredients from around the world. Choose a wine from our inspiring selection and simply enjoy the fine food. The Helenia home bistro is famous for its Sous vide - is a method of cooking food sealed in airtight plastic bags in a water bath or in a temperature-controlled steam environment for longer than normal cooking times. The intent is to cook the item evenly, ensuring that the inside is properly cooked without overcooking the outside, and retain moisture. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit B, Tin Hau MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3446, 'en_US', 'ANA Gura', 'ANA Gura adheres to the spirit of Japanese cuisine – fresh.', 'Prime fatty tuna, Snow crab claw with sea urchin tempura, Eel Teppanyaki', '', 'ANA Gura is located at Lan Kwai Fong in Central Point, senior Japanese possession, adhering to the essence of Japanese food from time to time, Japan sent fresh ingredients straight to the ANA Gura restaurant every day, cooking the most delicious seasonal dishes. We introduced Omi cattle than people, the Japanese special stoves heated to 180 degrees, with the Japanese air fresh sesame seed oil production, the thin outer layer of crisp pulp wrapped with fresh beef, gravy locked by high temperature, so that special taste level is clear to tell from every diner who have tried it. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3447, 'en_US', 'Teppanyaki Sessyu', 'In professional Teppanyaki restaurant, Japanese chefs will make authentic Teppanyaki for Hong Kong people in person.', 'Hokkaido king crab, Assorted sashimi', '', 'SESSYU is the first professional Kaiseki Teppanyaki restaurant in Hong Kong. Teppanyaki in Hong Kong so far is treated as one of Japanese cuisines, by which chef cooks on iron plate. SESSYU, which has been exposed in Hong Kong magazines for many times and attracted concern from the public, is the first professional restaurant to make Kaiseki Teppanyaki unique in Hong Kong. In professional Teppanyaki restaurant, Japanese chefs will make authentic Teppanyaki for Hong Kong people in person. In the past, Japanese Teppanyaki is the integration of western cuisine and Japanese cuisine. In SESSYU, you can enjoy the cuisine with French and Japanese features cooked by Japanese chefs who have studied in Europe. There are set meals and single dishes for you to choose. You can enjoy the French-style and Japanese cuisine. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3448, 'en_US', 'RA Restaurant & Lounge', 'Innovative fusion of Moroccan cuisine along with exotic belly dancer shows daily.', 'RA’s Signature Middle Eastern mixed grill platter, Seafood mixed grill, Couscous Royale', '', 'Named after the ancient Egyptian Sun God, RA Restaurant and Lounge is located along the bustling stretch of sea front bars and restaurants in Tsim Shat Tsui East. RA redefines alfresco dining with stunning harbor views, inspired interiors and its innovative fusion of Moroccan cuisine along with exotic belly dancer shows daily. RA presents three dynamic dining and lounging spaces. The indoor dining area is a dimly lit sitting surrounded by contemporary Egyptian stone carvings. The Private room – styled like a Moroccan den, is designed for intimate meals and private functions. The outdoor – a spacious seated area where guests can indulge in cool cocktails and fruit flavored Shishas /Hookahs (Egyptian water pipe) while taking in uninterrupted harbor views. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit P1, Tsim Sha Tsui East MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3449, 'en_US', 'Libertine', 'Libertine is a casual neighbourhood continental bistro.', 'Brunch, Oysters on the half shell', '', 'Libertine is a casual neighbourhood continental bistro located at the entrance of the Police Married Quarters on Aberdeen Street in SOHO. The kitchen serves a menu of traditional bistro fare that include our classic Steak Tartare, Moules Mariniere, Duck Leg Confit and Steak Frites as well as wines by the carafe and a range of signature cocktails. Libertine is open for brunch, lunch, dinner and late night cocktails. Libertine is about Breakfast, Brunch, Burgers, French and Seafood. Modeled after iconic French Bistros that dot the street of Paris, Libertine has that flair of \"Je ne sais quoi.\" Come in for a romantic date or to catch up with friends and we\'ll transport you to the City of Lights! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3450, 'en_US', 'Xuan Sushi', 'Xuan Sushi serves the meal of OMAKASE with fresh ingredients.', 'Omakase', '', 'Xuan Sushi provides different kinds of sashimi, sushi and seafood, located in Parekh House opposite the former police station on Wyndham Street. Xuan Sushi uses the fresh ingredients delivered from Japan day after day. It is an amazing sushi restaurant, highly recommended. It serves the meal of “OMAKASE”. The chef will generally present a series of plates, beginning with the lightest fare and proceeding to heaviest, richest dishes. Customers ordering omakase style expect the chef to be innovative and surprising in the selection of dishes, and the meal can be likened to an artistic performance by the chef. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3451, 'en_US', 'Linguini Fini', 'Linguini Fini is an Italian restaurant rooted in New York culture.', 'Papardelle \"Nose To Tail\" Bolognese, 10, hour roasted pork belly, basil, fennel & red onion salad, chili mustard', '', 'Linguini Fini is an Italian restaurant rooted in New York culture. That means it\'s not short of raw American passion with a distinct sense of style and attitude. But that\'s just the surface stuff. When you dig a little deeper into what we\'re about, you\'ll discover the essence of authentic Italian food. It\'s fresh produce. It\'s locally-sourced and 100% home-made. It\'s no wonder a meal at Linguini Fini is full of flavor. Because Italian food tastes so much better when you know it\'s pure, real and here for the good of the planet. The proof is in the pasta. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '8-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3452, 'en_US', 'The News Room Diner', 'The News Room Diner brings all-day all-American comfort food to Quarry Bay.', 'The Waygu burger, \"The all American\" breakfast', '', 'Formerly known as The News Room, in 2014 The News Room Diner was born, bringing all-day all-American comfort food to Quarry Bay. The News Room serves British breakfast, brunch and sandwiches. Kickstart your week with a healthy choice for dinner! The News Room Diner\'s Salad has a little bit of spice and a whole lot of flavor! Side dishes are just as important as the main course. Order a side of our grilled corn, sweet and juicy and a healthy alternative! Burgers and beers are a couple that\'s meant to be together! Now when you order any of our juicy burgers, get a bottle of refreshing Tsing Tao. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit A, Quarry Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3453, 'en_US', 'Bistronomique', 'Bistronomique servers French dishes, the environment is reassuring with concise décor.', 'Lobster Linguine, Grilled pork chop with mixed vegetables salad', '', 'Bistronomique is located in Kennedy Town, the environment is reassuring with concise décor, simple yet classy environment. As we walk inside we notice the high ceilings, the long dining room is filled in tones of cream and gives us a comfy ambience. The spicy kick of Chorizo works brilliantly with seafood especially squid. Bring the spicy flavour to the table with this intense, smoky starter just add with crusty bread will build up your appetite. Boudin basque is a standout blood and pig head sausage with espellete pepper serve with scallion mashed potatoes which melt in mouth. Don\'t forget to wash it down with a beer or wine from our selection of wine list. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit C, Kennedy Town MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3454, 'en_US', 'Bistronomique Staunton', 'Bistronomique servers French dishes, the environment is reassuring with concise décor.', 'Roe crab paella, Lobster risotto, Roasted Pigeon', '', 'Bistronomique Staunton is located in Central’s Staunton Street, l the environment is reassuring with concise décor, The spicy kick of Chorizo works brilliantly with seafood especially squid. Bring the spicy flavour to the table with this intense, smoky starter just add with crusty bread will build up your appetite. Boudin basque is a standout blood and pig head sausage with espellete pepper serve with scallion mashed potatoes which melt in mouth. Don\'t forget to wash it down with a beer or wine from our selection of wine list. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '9-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3455, 'en_US', 'Trattoria Doppio Zero', 'Doppio serves handmade pasta, powerful Italian recipes and seasonal ingredients.', 'Truffled fried oysters, Beetroot Ravioli, Grilled USDA prime ribeye (10 oz)', '', 'We at Doppio Zero live by three basic principles: handmade pasta, powerful Italian recipes and seasonal ingredients. We are the makers of the best fresh pasta in town, faithful practitioners and collectors of old world recipes, and relentless in pursuit of the freshest and best tasting ingredients we can get our hands on. Doppio Zero is elegant and modern while maintaining a warm and congenial atmosphere, truly living by the \"Trattoria\" code and being Sheung Wan\'s neighborhood restaurant. We offer a seasonal Italian menu featuring both fresh and dry pastas. Come join us for lunch or dinner; or stop by for a quartino of wine or dessert and see our rotating exhibit by local artists. Delivery and takeaway is available as well. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3456, 'en_US', 'Kushiyaki Beco', 'Kushiyaki Beco is a sweet ghetto-chic eatery that serves up some of the best kushiyaki in town.', 'Wagyu Rump Skewer, US rib eye skewer, Wagyu short rib skewer', '', 'If you’re looking to try your taste buds on a cool Japanese-style Yule, Kushiyaki Beco is a sweet ghetto-chic eatery that serves up some of the best kushiyaki in town. We are inviting you to come try out an alternative festive meal. Kushiyaki means skewer-grilled while Beco means beef and this combination is their claim to fame. They use only the best Australian Wagyu and are experts in skewer-grilling it to perfection. What matters most to us is your feedback. Visit us become even better by dropping me any suggestion you may have. I look forward to meeting you and hope you find great food wherever you may be. One of the best places for beef skewers in town, definitely worths for revisiting! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3457, 'en_US', 'Ginza Okura', 'Ginza Okura Japanese Restaurant provides quality of the food and the attentive service.', 'Okura style sushi, especially kohada and saba sushi, Teppanyaki wagyu beef, Stewed red snapper head', '', 'Ginza Okura Japanese Restaurant provides quality of the food and the attentive service. Chef Wong stacked beef with whiskey and set them alight and he got support from a group of former colleagues, all have over 20 years of experience of making Japanese dish. The chef of this restaurant used to be the head chef of the old \"Intercontinental Hotel\" and decided to run his own business. He is from japan and had been in Hong Kong for more than forty years. His Cantonese is pretty good so if you have any question about the menu or the recommendations, he could help you out. The place is lightening, clean and spacious. Also provided with a sashimi counter and let diners to order food straight from the chef. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit P3, Tsim Sha Tsui East MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3458, 'en_US', 'LUX Bar & Tapas', 'LUX - Bar & Tapas, boasting European cuisine with a modern touch.', 'Whole Boston lobster cocktail with champagne shallot vinegar and hot sauce, Chargrilled NZ lamb rack', '', 'Located in the heart of the bustling Lan Kwai Fong, LUX - Bar & Tapas, boasting European cuisine with a modern touch, is the perfect dining spot and your ideal place \"to see\" and \"be seen\". Featuring an al-fresco design, the lower floor bar area is a zone for relaxation. Having delighted discerning diners at some of the finest restaurants in Lan Kwai Fong for over 10 years, Executive Chef Alex Liu flourishes with exceptional culinary skills and food knowledge. Using only the freshest ingredients to combine with his unique culinary skill, Alex excels in creating European dishes that will deliver a lasting impression. As one of Lan Kwai Fong’s most popular bars, LUX will never be short of the best selections of wines from all over the world. From House Creations, Award Winning Cocktails, Molecular Infused to Vintage Beverages, the team of bartenders at LUX is always ready to inspire you with flavours that you will never forget. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3459, 'en_US', 'Kyoto Joe', 'Kyoto Joe’s creations are the perfect blend of traditional Japanese fare with a modern twist.', 'Oven baked silver cod in saikyo miso, Grilled beef ribs, Kyoto salad', '', 'Modern Japanese restaurant in Central. Savour a creative menu of the freshest sushi, sashimi and rolls, perfectly complimented by an array of delicious cooked dishes from the Robatayaki grill and full kitchen. Finish with a piping bowl of ramen or udon to leave all your senses completely satisfied. Using the finest ingredients, Kyoto Joe’s creations are the perfect blend of traditional Japanese fare with a modern twist.The exquisite decor inspired by the Kosodo Kimono from the Heian period provides multiple dining options, from an intimate dinner for two to a rowdy party in one of our private rooms. Not to be missed: Kyoto Salad, Chopped Salmon on Rice Cracker, Kobe Gyu Sushi Roll, Spicy Ramen and all our seasonal specials. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '4-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3460, 'en_US', 'Papi (Element Branch)', 'Papi ensures that every dish is tasted and every guest is satisfied, truly sharing a dining experience.', 'Linguine with sea urchins, Black truffle and Gorgonzola cheese pizza, Pan fried Hokkaido sea scallop', '', 'Papi is importing the latest culinary trend of “small-plate” dining to the tables of Hong Kong! The concept of Papi’s bite-sized items stems from the traditional way of eating across Italy, families taking time to share big meals of home-cooked delicious food together. Here at Papi’s Restaurant, we stay true to this way of life, encouraging Hong Kong diners to make Papi their home-away-from-home and enjoy sharing the best of traditional Italian fare. At Papi’s we offer a sophisticated small-plate approach for true Italian cuisine lovers, presenting a range of fresh, seasonal starter-size dishes under ‘Finger Food’ and ‘Fork Food’, alongside signature Pizzas and Pastas that can be shared over great conversation around the table. This way of eating is customary throughout Italy, ensuring that every dish is tasted and every guest is satisfied, truly sharing a dining experience whilst engaging and interacting with loved ones. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C2, Kowloon MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3461, 'en_US', 'Papi (QRE Plaza Branch)', 'Papi ensures that every dish is tasted and every guest is satisfied, truly sharing a dining experience.', 'Linguine with sea urchins, Black truffle and Gorgonzola cheese pizza, Pan fried Hokkaido sea scallop', '', 'Papi is importing the latest culinary trend of “small-plate” dining to the tables of Hong Kong! The concept of Papi’s bite-sized items stems from the traditional way of eating across Italy, families taking time to share big meals of home-cooked delicious food together. Here at Papi’s Restaurant, we stay true to this way of life, encouraging Hong Kong diners to make Papi their home-away-from-home and enjoy sharing the best of traditional Italian fare. At Papi’s we offer a sophisticated small-plate approach for true Italian cuisine lovers, presenting a range of fresh, seasonal starter-size dishes under ‘Finger Food’ and ‘Fork Food’, alongside signature Pizzas and Pastas that can be shared over great conversation around the table. This way of eating is customary throughout Italy, ensuring that every dish is tasted and every guest is satisfied, truly sharing a dining experience whilst engaging and interacting with loved ones. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B2, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3462, 'en_US', 'Okinawa Dining BRIDGES', 'Okinawa Dining BRIDGES introduces the traditional Okinawa lifestyle to Hong Kong.', 'Grilled Okinawa pork knuckle with salt, Okinawa AGU pork and vegetables steamed hot pot, Grilled red king crab with salt', '', 'The atmosphere oozes contemporary style with its image, motifs and materials used while introducing the traditional Okinawa lifestyle to Hong Kong. Ships up freshly flown Okinawa ingredients into healthy yet mouth watering dishes. Okinawa Dining BRIDGES emulates a celebration for life, a gathering place and fate, all in perfect harmony. We aim to share with the world our ideal, dedication and zest for the food and culture of Japan and Okinawa. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3463, 'en_US', 'The Square', 'The Square is with time-honed craft turns raw stone into precious jade; a delicate process with no tolerance for impurities.', 'Sautéed lobster balls with crab meat and crab roe sauce, Fresh crab claw and bamboo pith in clear soup, Bird’s nest stuffed in bamboo pith with crab meat and crab roe', '', 'In 2010, The Square is re-launched with a whole new look, with time-honed craft turns raw stone into precious jade; a delicate process with no tolerance for impurities. One of the four major cuisines in China, Cantonese Cuisine is characterized by its variety and freshness of ingredients, and range of cooking styles. Cantonese Cuisine is also known for being seasonal – light dishes are served in Summer and Autumn, rich dishes in Winter and Spring. Famous Cantonese dishes include braised shark\'s fin soup, steamed seafood, baked lobster in soup, snake\'s meat thick soup, salt-baked chicken, winter melon bowl soup, and braised belly pork with taro. There is of course the not-to-be-missed Cantonese dim sum and barbecued meats that give Cantonese cuisine its global reputation. Awarded with world-famous Michelin Star for three years in a row since 2009 for its premium services, elegant comfortable environment, and top-notch gastronomic experience, The Square will continue to carry on this world-class dining tradition in perfection. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit A, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3464, 'en_US', 'Fa Zu Jie', 'Fa Zu Jie is the name of private home cuisine, reflecting the characteristics of dishes.', 'Diana spicy slow, cooked beef. Wonton, sticky prawn', '', 'Fa Zu Jie is the name of private home cuisine, reflecting the characteristics of dishes - a fusion of Chinese and western cuisine, accompanied by exquisite French cuisine and delicate in color, flavor and traditional Shanghai cuisine. Fa Zu Jie private home cuisine provides comfortable environment, like eating at home, comfortably wide but a little more the taste at home that you eat. Food is very creative, such as slow-cooked with Japanese quail drunk cold Sanuki udon noodles, lentils Pickled garlic crab with flat pasta and so on. Overall, Fa Zu Jie, good service attitude, to make a detailed presentation of dishes, it is very live to be, because the menu description alone it is hard to imagine due the name of dishes. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3465, 'en_US', 'Hooray Bar & Restaurant', 'Hooray Bar & Restaurant is a great spot to indulge in a long lunch or luxuriate in a chic evening gathering.', 'Pan seared foie gras with Sicilian lemon jam, yuzu sorbet and pomegranate dressing, Grill US Prime Rib, eye', '', 'Hooray Bar & Restaurant boasts the biggest alfresco dining area in Hong Kong, with a spectacular terrace that overlooks Victoria Harbour. The elegant wood furniture on the 180-seat terrace is surrounded by luscious foliage, creating a relaxing respite from the bustling city below. The fabulous charcoal grill menu provides delectable vegetarian, seafood and meat dishes, making Hooray a great spot to indulge in a long lunch or luxuriate in a chic evening gathering. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D4, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3466, 'en_US', 'Casa Fina Seafood & Oyster Bar', 'Casa Fina Seafood & Oyster Bar is located in Causeway Bay provides freshly-opened oysters.', 'Oyster, Spaghetti with sea urchins, Risotto with scallop in ink sauce', '', 'Casa Fina Seafood & Oyster Bar is located in Causeway Bay, if you come here, of course you have to try the freshly-opened oysters by yourself, pattern chic restaurants, the main entrance where there is a small opening oysters counter bar where you can see the chef in the kitchen through the glass case when they are opening the oysters. The restaurant every night has different kinds of oysters buy one get promotions, many types of oysters, there are more than half a dozen oysters from Japan, the US, South Africa, England, Scotland, Ireland, France. After eating raw oysters served with a sauce, but I think it is the authentic flavor of the oysters without any sauce taste better! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3467, 'en_US', 'Casa de Peace', 'Casa de Peace is a new Western-style restaurant.', 'Crème brûlée, Grilled Prime Grade Rib, eye urchins red wine sauce with Italian baked rice, Scallop with Boudin Salad', '', 'Casa de Peace in Causeway Bay on Hong Kong Island, the origin of its name is derived from the Spanish, Casa means \"home\" and \"Peace\" construed quiet peace. The restaurant serves lunch and dinner menu, change the menu and once a month, the bread is hand-made by the chef, sincerity incense and incense, guests can cater to the taste, but also give guests fresh each time. Coupled with the clerk gratification care, plus the environment make diners have a feeling of relaxation. The owner is hoped that guests can come to live in a both comfortable, and quiet dining environment, the general feel as their own home, feeling relaxed! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3468, 'en_US', 'Grand Central Bar & Grill', 'Grand Central is a stylish 2-story restaurant offering American fare.', 'Chilled seafood platter, Black Mussels, Crab cake', '', 'Grand Central is a stylish 2-story restaurant, popular with the finance industry professionals, Elements shoppers & Kowloon residents to enjoy a bite to eat in an urban atmosphere. Offering American fare, we are not only a sport fan’s hangout, after work “watering hole” and weekend brunch spot but more importantly a popular even destination. You can enjoy a great cocktail, pint or fine glass of wine and extensive range of premium imported micro - brewery beers and niche drafts from all over the word with friends after a hard day work, or doing the power - lunch/dinner, especially as guests can be assured of the great quality and value for money offerings. Our friendly staff, lively atmosphere and great USA food. GC brings only the best in upscale casual drinking, dining and premium sports to its highest level in Kowloon, Hong Kong and is a “must experience ” place! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C2, Kowloon MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3469, 'en_US', 'Kazuo Okada', 'Kazuo Okada promotes WASHOKU, to satisfy all the food lovers in town.', 'Kisetsu, no, otidoke, Salad of 10 organic vegetables, Deep, fried shrimp tataki and seaweed', '', 'Kazuo Okada is committed to promote WASHOKU, to satisfy all the food lovers in town. The chef uses only the best and freshest seasonal ingredients to prepare the menu, importing all the ingredients from Japan. The ingredients like kelp and dried bonito flake have been chosen strictly, and stress a lot on enhancing diners’ five senses by balancing the taste, texture, appearance and colors of ingredients perfectly to present the Dashi. Chef Hirofumi Imamura believes every dish should stimulate each of the five senses, even including texture of ingredients and the sounds diners make while being enjoyed. Besides, the age of our “Edo era utensil” is over than 200 years, serving the cuisine by using above utensil could spread out the Japanese culture to our customers. Through the open kitchen, diner can explore all the cooking steps and see executive chef performing his magic. And chef will serve different menu to guests according to their age and preference. Guests can rest assured to expect nothing but the finest WASHOKU cuisine at Kazuo Okada. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '15-min walk from Exit B1, Hung Hom MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3470, 'en_US', 'Joia', 'Joia is a sophisticated, business casual restaurant offering relaxed dining in a rooftop garden setting.', 'Red prawns tartar with avocado and green apple sherbet, Spaghetti with fresh Boston lobster in tomato and basil, Florentine steak', '', 'Joia (translated as ‘joy’ in Italian) is a sophisticated, business casual restaurant offering relaxed dining in a rooftop garden setting. With a contemporary modern feel and a menu that gives a fresh twist to authentic Northern Italian cuisine, Joia is as well suited to dining with family and friends as business entertaining, whether for a weekday lunch or dinner or weekend brunch. Gaia Group was founded in Hong Kong in 2000, with its first venture being the opening of the ultra glamorous Gaia restaurant in a prestigious new commercial development at 181 Queens Road Central. Beside the Italian-inspired Millennium Square piazza complete with its own \'Spanish Steps\' and tiered fountain, Gaia - complete with its stylish al fresco dining in an environment uncannily reminiscent of Rome - immediately became one of Hong Kong’s top Italian restaurants. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C2, Kowloon MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3471, 'en_US', 'Zelo Spanish Restaurant & Tapas Bar', 'Zelo is Chic, Sophisticated and Contemporary Spanish Cuisine.', 'Noemi, style Caesar salad, Sautéed Iberian pork chops with mango and pumpkin puree pea, Paella negra', '', 'Seamlessly flowing spaces and a light indoor/outdoor feel accented with natural, reclaimed materials makes this contemporary restaurant and bar the embodiment of casual urban ‘eco-chic’. A relaxed atmosphere, all day menu of modern Spanish cuisine and great cocktails and wines by the glass make Zelo an ideal retreat at any time of day. The latest venture by Gaia Group - creators of acclaimed Italian restaurants Isola and Gaia - Zelo is a chic andsophisticated, contemporary restaurant and bar serving innovative, world-class Spanish cuisine. By day, the restaurant’s seamlessly flowing spaces and airy indoor/outdoor feel embodies casual urban elegance. Whilst by night, whimsically ethereal touches accented by natural, reclaimed materials create a mood of inviting intimacy. As well suited to afternoon tea as after-work drinks, Zelo’s relaxed atmosphere and variety of menus available throughout the day makes it the perfect escape; definitely one of Hong Kong’s most exciting new dining destinations. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit F, Admiralty MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3472, 'en_US', 'Yu Lei Chinese Restaurant', 'Yu Lei presents gorgeous performance of Shanghainese dishes and combined the delicate essence of Japan.', 'Drunken Kyushu crab, Steamed rice with cod and conpoy in bamboo basket, Crispy sweet and sour pork with three types of vinegar', '', 'Yu Lei offers unique and traditional Shanghainese cuisine creatively prepared by Japanese Chef Miki Imagawa, who presented gorgeous performance of Shanghainese dishes and combined the delicate essence of Japan. Chef Miki, who is renowned for presenting the authentic tastes of traditional dishes as works of visual art with his creativity. He was the first Japanese Michelin-starred chef specialized in Chinese cuisine. He also pays close attention to every ingredient, seasoning and garnishing and cooking method to create perfectly balanced dishes. The Shanghainese supreme soup to be of utmost importance for it has tremendous impact on taste. While chef spends a lot effort on refining the soup. Apart from the superb Shanghainese dishes, Yu Lei also serves sumptuous Cantonese dim sum and barbecued meat. The décor theme of Yu Lei is “Garden”. There are five VIP dining rooms, each designed around a particular flower with a specially designed chandelier and murals. Diners can enjoy lunch and dinner with stunning panoramic view of Victoria Harbour. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '15-min walk from Exit B1, Hung Hom MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3473, 'en_US', 'Bella Vita', 'Bella Vita embodies all the characteristics of Italian lifestyle - friends, family, delicious food and beautiful wines.', 'Crispy Iberico suckling pig with shaved fennel and orange, Linguini with jumbo red prawn, date tomato and garlic, Fiorentina T, bone Porterhouse steak', '', 'Bella Vita embodies all the characteristics of Italian lifestyle - friends, family, delicious food and beautiful wines. As one of the foremost restaurants in town, the popular Italian restaurant Bella Vita tranforms into a top upscale steakhouse, beefs up its menu by putting a focus on supreme beef. Simple, true and honest, with a beautiful heart and beautiful ingredients, are born beautiful dishes. The venue Designed by renowned interior designer Mr. Steve Leung and endowed with the exceptional lightings by international recognized lighting consultant Mr. Tino Kwan, the restaurant is emerged in a cozy ambience modeled after the idyllic essence of Tuscan countryside. Utensils brought by Francesco from his home and antique Italian cabinets enrich the classic Tuscan beauty while the painted wall in the private room lively portrays the natural atmosphere of Tuscany. Diners can simply enjoy a unique al fresco dining experience at the terrace, drinking in the refreshing beauty of an urban oasis. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3474, 'en_US', 'Shore Steak', 'Relax and unwind in a nice urban oasis atmosphere.', 'In, house dry, aged steaks, Signature steak tartar, Pan, seared scallops with sea urchin sauce', '', 'Shore, where water meets the land, is named after the confluence of its ‘onshore’ main dining room on 4th floor and ‘offshore’ lounge area on 3rd floor of the L. place. The ‘offshore’ lounge is designed for entertaining and networking. Its concept of a natural sea is enhanced with modern geometry and texture of sedimentary rocks form the columns. The bar runs from entrance of the terrace through the very back of the space. Spanning its extensive length, the lounge becomes the perfect any-occasion venue for corporate functions, private parties and happy hour with friends. The spacious 1,800 sq. ft. outdoor terrace with comfortable sofas, high tables and round booth seating is ideal for alfresco social gatherings, casual lunches and corporate parties, providing a breath of fresh air for those who want to relax and unwind in a nice urban oasis atmosphere.', '5-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3475, 'en_US', 'Gonpachi', 'The dining experience at Gonpachi is a celebration of rich Japanese culture and traditions.', 'Assorted Tempura, Kani Soba Buckwheat noodle with crab sticks and mushrooms in hot broth, Premium Beef Sirloin Steak Char, grilled Miyazaki A5', '', 'Gonpachi is named after “Shirai Gonpachi”, the main character of a Kabuki, a form of traditional Japanese theatre. The dining experience at Gonpachi is a celebration of rich Japanese culture and traditions. Taking the best of traditional Japanese cuisine to a whole new level, Gonpachi serves hand-pounded home-made buckwheat soba noodles and “kushi”-style skewered delicacies using the finest ingredients brought in directly from Japan. Famous for his good looks, bravery and swordsmanship. Gonpachi’s story is one that challenges the moral values of one faced with love and passion. Seamlessly blending tradition and uniqueness in their dining experience, a variety of innovative dishes are available at Gonpachi in addition to traditional Japanese flavours. With an eye to perfection, the restaurant is a feast both to the eyes and to the palate. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit F1, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3476, 'en_US', 'Sorabol Korean Restaurant (Causeway Bay Restaurant)', 'Our Korean chef personally maintains the quality and taste for which Sorabol is famous for.', 'King, size marinated top grade short ribs, Rice mixed with vegetables and beef in stone pot, Palace, style stewed beef short ribs', '', 'Since the opening of its first branch in the central area of Kowloon Peninsula, Hong Kong in 1993, Sorabol has opened restaurants in Hong Kong, Shenzhen, and Guangzhou. We work in conjunction with Beijing Sorabol to lead the promotion of Korean cuisine in China and elsewhere. Sorabol was a name of the city, Kyung-ju, which was the capital of Shilla Dynasty, the first nation to achieve unification of Korea, and the name of today\'s capital, Seoul originates from it. Our brand logo is an image of the equestrian statue, the 91st national treasure which symbolizes the cultural prosperity in Shilla Dynasty, emphasizing the service of the best quality we provide. We use ingredients that are imported and delivered from Korea and organic vegetables raised locally in our own Sorabol Farm located in the mountains of Huizhou, China. Our Korean chef personally maintains the quality and taste for which Sorabol is famous for. Our priority is the enjoyment and health of our customer. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit A, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3477, 'en_US', 'Sorabol Korean Restaurant (Tsim Sha Tsui Branch)', 'Our Korean chef personally maintains the quality and taste for which Sorabol is famous for.', 'King, size marinated top grade short ribs, Rice mixed with vegetables and beef in stone pot, Palace, style stewed beef short ribs', '', 'Since the opening of its first branch in the central area of Kowloon Peninsula, Hong Kong in 1993, Sorabol has opened restaurants in Hong Kong, Shenzhen, and Guangzhou. We work in conjunction with Beijing Sorabol to lead the promotion of Korean cuisine in China and elsewhere. Sorabol was a name of the city, Kyung-ju, which was the capital of Shilla Dynasty, the first nation to achieve unification of Korea, and the name of today\'s capital, Seoul originates from it. Our brand logo is an image of the equestrian statue, the 91st national treasure which symbolizes the cultural prosperity in Shilla Dynasty, emphasizing the service of the best quality we provide. We use ingredients that are imported and delivered from Korea and organic vegetables raised locally in our own Sorabol Farm located in the mountains of Huizhou, China. Our Korean chef personally maintains the quality and taste for which Sorabol is famous for. Our priority is the enjoyment and health of our customer. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit B1, Tsim Sha Tsui MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3478, 'en_US', 'St. Betty', 'St Betty is a smart casual modern European restaurant overlooking Victoria harbour.', 'Sautéed spätzle with wild mushrooms, fresh black truffle, Taleggio cheese, Pan, fried prawns with crisp pork belly, Passionfruit soufflé', '', 'St Betty is a smart casual modern European restaurant overlooking Victoria harbour.\n \'Design Master\' Andre Fu created the \'cucina rustica\' dining space with travertino stones and tungsten pendants, further embellished by full, dramatic harbour views.\n St Betty offers both a la carte and set lunch menu for Monday - Friday, brunch menu on Saturday and Sunday and a la carte menu for dinner. Afternoon Tea is served daily from 3pm - 6pm. Get a kick from our espresso-based cocktail drinks - espresso martini made with patron silver coffee tequila, Irish coffee made with whiskey or shakerato made with Kahlua. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit A2, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3479, 'en_US', 'Madam Sixty Ate', 'A restaurant for every occasion, Madam Sixty Ate is a fantastic location in the hip and happening scene of Wan Chai dining.', 'Duck breast, black pudding, pickled cherries and port wine, Confit mackerel with cucumber gazpacho and apple celeriac salad, Summer strawberries, honey yoghurt and coconut meringue', '', 'A restaurant for every occasion, Madam Sixty Ate is a fantastic location in the hip and happening scene of Wan Chai dining. Opened by husband-and-wife team Chris Woodyard and Bronwyn Cheung of Woolly Pig Concepts, Madam Sixty Ate is a relaxed, casual space offering a luxury food experience. At Madam Sixty Ate, we believe in creating dishes with flavor. The interiors of Madam Sixty Ate are stylish and modern, reminiscent of a comfortably well-appointed apartment space with 80 seats indoors and 25 al fresco seats. Whimsical portraits and memorabilia from Madam’s international travels are depicted on the menu and artworks, such as Joseph (the duck), Eliza (the Woolly pig), Pedro (the squid), Sophie (the rabbit) and Stanley (the snapper), which are also incorporated into menu items. The restaurant caters to all experiences, with a weekly changing set lunch as well as brunch and afternoon tea on weekends. Dinner is available seven days for a casual dinner with friends or a special celebration. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B2, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3480, 'en_US', 'Madam S\'ate', 'Madam S’ate is an elegant modern bar and a welcoming dining room.', 'Seabass with pickled fennel, red peppers, herbs and rouille, The Sate’d Wagyu Cheeseburger, Sirloin USDA Prime', '', 'Ideally located in the upcoming neighbourhood of Kowloon West at Elements, between the Ritz Carlton, W Hotel and the ICC Madam S’ate features an extensive outdoor terrace, an elegant modern bar and a welcoming dining room. To satisfy all tastes, the French inspired bistro menu devised by culinary director Christopher Woodyard contains classics such as duck l’orange; braised citrus duck and sweet potato bread or for a more hearty option Wagyu steak, confit eschallots and bearnaise. For the healthy diner a selection of salads such as French heirloom tomatotes, crotin goats cheese and oregano will also be popular. Old time favourite desserts, tarte tatin of seasonal fruits or lemon tart can never be forgotten.Madam S’ate comprehensive wine list will be feature the best of new world and old world varietals focusing on 45 different options. Half of the list will be available by the glass ensuring everyone has a great choice on a sunny weekend afternoon or weekday night. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit C2, Kowloon MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3481, 'en_US', 'Harvey Nichols Fourth Floor Restaurant & Bar', 'Harvey Nichols Fourth Floor Restaurant & Bar offers dishes that match modern flavours with traditional techniques.', 'Foie gras terrine with pumpkin souffle, scallop & vegetables, Butter poached lobster and steamed sea bass with ozetto pasta, Pan, fried US prime beef tenderloin and caramelised foie gras', '', 'Harvey Nichols Fourth Floor Restaurant & Bar offers the ultimate dining experience, It produces to create dishes that match modern flavours with traditional techniques. The design for the Window Bar highlights the stunning picture window, with its incredible views. Subtle lighting and chilled-out music, along with one of the most creative and forward-thinking cocktail menus, combine to create one of the best drinking scenes in the city centre. Our modern British dishes are seasonal and beautifully presented with an innovative twist. The Restaurant also offers a superb vegetarian/vegan menu. The Bar is open to the public with no reservation required. The bar closes to non-diners when it reaches capacity, so we do always recommend calling ahead to check if we are full. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '2-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3482, 'en_US', 'Bishoku Club Yoshida', 'Bishoku Club Yoshida with the agenda of The Beauty of Japanese Food to the World.', 'Kobe beef roll with sea urchin, Kobe beef sirloin steak, Hanami, Chicken Terriyaki', '', 'Bishoku Club Yoshida always reminds ourselves of our main agenda “The Beauty of Japanese Food to the World”, we will focus again on our effort to reach the goal. We appreciate again for your continuous support and reinforcement.We would like to take this opportunity to thank you very much for all of your continuous patronage, support, and encouragement for our restaurant this past year.Our main agenda is continuously to serve you with our very best this year again to satisfy your needs. Please come join us to enjoy delicious dishes from Tochigi prefecture. As we appreciate your enormous support. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Exit G, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3483, 'en_US', 'Megan\'s Kitchen', 'Megan\'s Kitchen is famous for innovative hot pot soup base such as Tomato and Crab Soup.', 'Tomato and crab soup in soufflé finish, Rainbow cuttlefish balls, Sautéed spare ribs with strawberries', '', 'Nice décor and cosy ambience with a little western fine dining design. All tables are fitted with induction cookers which are safe and easy to use. There are VIP rooms equipped with toliets and LCD TVs for added privacy and comfort. We are famous for: innovative hot pot soup base such as Tomato and Crab Soup Base with Souffle Finish healthy meatballs with special fillings such as cuttlefish balls with cherry tomato, etc.We provide a huge selection of beef from local markets, Australia, USA as well as Japan ! The selection includes sirloin, rib eye, beef tongue, beef cheek, etc. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '6-min walk from Exit A3, Wan Chai MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3484, 'en_US', 'The Peak Lookout', 'The Peak Lookout offers a wide selection of international cuisine.', 'Hainan chicken rice, Tandoori lamb shoulder, Seafood platter', '', 'An iconic Hong Kong landmark located in a heritage building with stunning sea views, the Peak Lookout offers a wide selection of international cuisine, including sushi, curry, tandoori, pasta, grilled dishes, steak, seafood and vegetarian items, the restaurant caters to all tastes. Its relaxing, comfortable dining area makes it the perfect location to unwind before your journey begins. It also offers a private room which is ideal for business meetings and private gatherings. The Peak Lookout offers fine food in an atmosphere of relaxation and elegance with a warm welcome and friendly service. Our extensive menu features elegant Asian favourites, classic Western dishes, jet-fresh seafood items at oyster bar, open-flame charcoal barbecue items and an exciting range of our own Peak Lookout specialties. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '- The Peak Tram on Garden Road, Central\n- No 1 green mini bus from IFC minibus depot \n- No 15 The Peak bus from Exchange Square', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3485, 'en_US', 'Mekiki no Ginji (Causeway Bay Branch)', 'Mekiki no Ginji boasts traditional Japanese dishes with a modern touch and a relaxing ambience full of vibe.', 'Grilled rice ball with spicy cod roe and butter, Chicken meat udon nooles in chicken soup, Salt grilled arabesque greenling', '', 'Mekiki no Ginji hails directly from Okinawa Japan is a rapidly growing dining establishment that boasts traditional Japanese dishes with a modern touch and a relaxing ambience full of vibe. Mekiki no Ginji has been growing since the flagship shop opened in Okinawa 8 years ago. The brand now owns more than 10 shops in Okinawa Japan and Hong Kong will be their first overseas attempt. The setting in Ginji sets a modern and convivial tone with clean furnishings. Inviting you to the restaurant is a line of big wooden barrel that boasts a sharp Japanese sense and a gigantic U-shape wooden table that showcases a colorful array of ingredients. The restaurant also makes use of live tempura, robatayaki, and sushi stations that invite you to the exciting dining scene. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D4, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
