(3508, 'en_US', 'CVCHE', 'CVCHE offers a fresh, innovative and daring take on seafood cuisine from all over the world.', 'Seafood platters, Fresh Oysters, Grilled French Sea Bass with Hand Made Gnocchi & Orange, Rosemary Butter', '', 'CVCHE offers a fresh, innovative and daring take on seafood cuisine from all over the world. Conveniently located in the heart of Hong Kong’s Lan Kwai Fong district, CVCHE is a seafood, oyster and wine bar that offers a creative twist on ocean flavors while offering each customer a unique culinary experience they will never forget. We pride ourselves on using the freshest, high quality ingredients from the most trusted food suppliers around the globe. CVCHE’s décor was designed with comfort, class and sophistication in mind. Featuring an open kitchen and a breath taking view of the bustling Central scene, LKF’s newest seafood restaurant offers an ambience that few in Hong Kong can match. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D2, Central MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3509, 'en_US', 'Magnolia', '\"Magnolia Private Kitchenis is where you can experience authentic New Orleans style Cajun and Creole cuisine.', 'Soft Shell Crabs Amandine, New Orleans Seafood Gumbo', '', 'Magnolia Private Kitchen is the hottest ‘dinner party’ private kitchen concept. We are open every Thursday, Friday and Saturday night by pre-booking only. It’s the only place in Hong Kong where you can experience authentic New Orleans style Cajun and Creole cuisine.\nMagnolia is the epitome of southern charm and grace. It takes the private kitchen concept to a whole new level. Coming to Magnolia is like going to a dinner party at a good friend’s home – who just happens to be a fantastic chef!\n It’s a dinner party for people who appreciate good food, good company and good fun. It’s a great venue for entertaining clients and friends alike. Magnolia features the award winning Cajun and Creole cuisine of Lori Granito, formerly of The Bayou Restaurant. She’ll serve up New Orleans favorites like Jambalaya, Crawfish Pie and File’ Gumbo each week. \nMagnolia is consistently rated as one of Hong Kong’s best private kitchens. Seating is limited, so be sure to book early! (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3511, 'en_US', 'Catch on Catchick', 'Catch On Catchick is located in Kennedy Town, with the outdoor environment and the white decoration, which makes it become very popular in Kennedy Town.', 'Catch fish & chips, beer battered sea perch, hand, cut chips, Seared scallops, cauliflower puree, crispy prosciutto, tomato, asparagus & fennel salsa, Big bad Ben Breakfast', '', 'Catch On Catchick is located in Kennedy Town, with the outdoor environment and the white decoration, which makes it become very popular in Kennedy Town. The restaurant dishes mainly focus on the taste, with the equal ratio for the starter, salad and main course. The most famous dish are the seafood, lamb chops and steaks. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit B, Kennedy Town MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3512, 'en_US', 'Eat Right', 'Eat Right is all about the goodness of healthy, organic food, served with zero MSG.', 'Grilled prawns w/ lime and jalapeno, Peking seared duck wolls w/ plum sauce, Swedish meatballs w/ mashed potatoes, gravy and lingonberries', '', 'Located in the heart of Soho, Eat Right is all about the goodness of healthy, organic food, served with zero MSG. Eat Right\'s nourishing menus are bursting with freshness and flavour, tempting your taste buds while taking good care of your waistline. With all dishes approved by in-house nutritional expert, you can be confident that every bite will be a guilt-free pleasure. Eat Right are always running special promotions to keep things fresh and exciting, so bookmark our website to stay on top of our regular updates. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit C, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3513, 'en_US', 'GLOW', 'GLOW, is an oyster bar and seafood grill located on Second Street in Sai Ying Pun.', 'Fresh Oyster, Lobster, Tiramisu', '', 'GLOW, which stands for “Grill Lounge Ocean Wine”, is an oyster bar and seafood grill located on Second Street in Sai Ying Pun. Owned by brothers Keith and Vincent Ng, they are clearly very passionate about what they’re doing and seem to have started on the right foot, given that the restaurant is busy every night of the week. GLOW definitely gives off an inviting charm from the exterior. Inside, light wood, faux-vintage mirrors and cosy booth seating take up most of the space, whilst along the bar, stools are set up for diners to gaze longingly at the fresh oysters, lobster, crab and clams. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '3-min walk from Eastern Street trams station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3514, 'en_US', 'Sushi Shota', 'With the best in service, the pursuit of perfection in serving Japanese traditional food and heartwarming atmosphere, the sophisticated elegant dining experience is assured at SUSHI SHOTA.', 'Sashimi & sushi set, Supreme Hokkai rice bowl', '', 'Located at the 8th floor of Kyoto Plaza, SUSHI SHOTA features a simple yet comfortable dining room, sushi bar and private dining room for special events. At sushi bar, diners can enjoy watching the devoted masters at work.\nOur Japanese Chef has long-term experience in making authentic sushi. We are believing that using the finest ingredients and seasonings are only the primary elements of serving fine Japanese food. Sushi Shota pays meticulous attention from choosing the freshest fish and condiment, to the method of dealing with ingredients. Small as the wasabi between sashimi and rice is also freshly ground by our chef. The artistic presentation and harmonic food combination impress many discerning diners.\nAs important as the delicate taste of the dish itself, the genuine hospitality also leaves diners in SUSHI SHOTA an unforgettable impression. With the best in service, the pursuit of perfection in serving Japanese traditional food and heartwarming atmosphere, the sophisticated elegant dining experience is assured at SUSHI SHOTA. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '1-min walk from Exit C, Causeway Bay MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
