(3986, 'en_US', 'Café de Paris', 'Café de Paris brings a Parisian touch to the popular Soho dining district.', 'Black Angus sirloin (10oz) with Cafe de Paris butter, Seafood bouillabaisse with saffron, fennel, carrots and rouille, Mussels \"Mariniere\" with onion, shallots, garlic, parsley, butter and white wine', '', 'Café de Paris brings a Parisian touch to the popular Soho dining district. It reflects the ambience of Parisian street cafes, where dark wood paneling, maroon coloured-walls and mirrors etched with decorative scrolls are displayed creating a warm and cozy atmosphere. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '9-min walk from Exit E1, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3987, 'en_US', 'Cafe Deco Pizzeria (Sheung Wan Branch)', 'Riding on the success of Cafe Deco Pizzeria in Elements, Cafe Deco Group has opened a new branch on island side for gourmands!', 'M6 wagyu beef and prawn pizza, Grilled chicken breast, The Duck pizza', '', 'Cafe Deco Pizzeria features a contemporary interior with wooden table tops, sleek chairs and stylish chandeliers. With an open pizza kitchen, friends and family alike can enjoy and relax while witnessing the making of the pizzas freshly from the ovens. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '10-min walk from Exit A2, Sheung Wan MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3989, 'en_US', 'Peak Cafe Bar (Central Branch)', 'The nostalgic decoration in Peak Cafe Bar is widely accepted as one of Soho\'s landmarks.', 'Grilled Boston Lobster Tail, Nasi Goreng, Peak Cafe Bar full breakfast', '', 'Peak Cafe Bar is an \"east meets west\" bar/restaurant concept by Cafe Deco Group. The nostalgic decoration is widely accepted as one of Soho\'s landmarks.\nNestled on the busy slopes of Soho, Hong Kong\'s most popular dining district, Peak Cafe Bar cascades alongside the world\'s longest escalator across a 3,500 sq ft area comprised of an indoor and outdoor bistro, a long bar and lounge and a garden courtyard, linking the two. Continuing the success, the restaurant amazes diners with succulent seafood and steamy-hot grill for a unique diner experience. Peak Cafe Bar offers a range of traditional cuisines from Chinese and Southeast Asian specialties, as well as salads, pizza and sandwiches. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '7-min walk from Exit C, Hong Kong MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3990, 'en_US', 'Peak Cafe Bar (Olympian City Branch)', 'Seafood and grill expert Peak Cafe Bar is thrilled to expand from Hong Kong Island to Kowloon at Olympian City!', 'Appetizer platter, Funghi Di Parma Pizza, Char, grilled Chimichurri Ribeye', '', 'Standing strong in Soho for over a decade after relocated from The Peak, seafood and grill expert Peak Cafe Bar is thrilled to expand from Hong Kong Island to Kowloon at Olympian City! Located in the heart of West Kowloon’s Olympian City, this new branch of Peak Cafe Bar offers a cosy and relaxing setting with a contemporary yet homey ambience, as well as an open kitchen for diners to witness the making of their alluring meals. Also, the restaurant’s private dining room is ideal for gatherings and parties, allowing small groups to enjoy the palatable relish in a more exclusive setting. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D3, Olympic MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(3991, 'en_US', 'Dim Sum Bar (Tsuen Wan Branch)', 'In Dim Sum Bar, diners can enjoy a complete meal by choosing dishes tapas-style and sharing.', 'Baked abalone and chicken pastry, King\'s dumplings in lobster bisque, Baked barbecue pork creak buns', '', 'Dim Sum Bar is no ordinary dim sum restaurant. The casual yet modern ambience offers a food paradise especially for dim sum lovers. Dim Sum Bar signature dim sum favorites include Baked Whole Abalone and Diced Chicken Pastry, Steamed Pork Dumplings with Truffles, King’s Dumplings in Lobster Bisque, Rice Rolls with assorted mushrooms, beef or barbecued pork, Wonton with Minced Pork and Foie Gras in Soup, Steamed Xian Long Bao with Mitten Crab Meat and King’s Dumpling in Supreme Soup. \nIn Dim Sum Bar, diners can enjoy a complete meal by choosing dishes tapas-style and sharing. (Contents and images are rightfully owned by undefined, if there is any concern, please contact us.)', '5-min walk from Exit D, Tsuen Wan West MTR Station', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
